This is your chance to network, showcase your startup, and hear from a curated lineup of founders ready to pitch their ideas. Whether you're refining your pitch, seeking feedback, or looking to connect with potential partners or investors, this event offers valuable insights and opportunities to move your startup forward.

column11: Haley Everheart (she/they) is VP of Marketing at FOLX Health, leading efforts to expand LGBTQIA+ healthcare access and bringing 15+ years of experience building mission-driven brands featured in Teen Vogue, CNN, Forbes, and more. Madison Butler is a Black, queer founder, speaker, and advocate who founded Blue Haired Unicorn to help startups and organizations build inclusive, psychologically safe workplaces; known for her bold voice on mental health and belonging, she‚Äôs been featured in The New York Times, WSJ, Fast Company, and named a LinkedIn Top Black Voice. Michael Sui (he/him, multiracial, queer) is a leader in inclusive design (and recovering perfectionist). Over 20+ years, he‚Äôs crafted brand and user experiences for companies including Google, YouTube, Airbnb, Nokia, and Pottery Barn. He co-organizes San Francisco‚Äôs 3,000-member A11yBay Meetup community, has guest lectured at the Stanford d. School, Berkeley Haas School of Business, Kapor Center, and graduated from Carnegie Mellon University. Obsidian Adebayo (they/she) is a Britgerian entrepreneur and strategist, currently Commercial Director at Q+ Consulting and founder of the Influence Index and Olorun, with work featured in major outlets like the Financial Times and BBC News. Dr. Hitesh Tolani founded Gays of National Parks to create inclusive outdoor spaces for LGBTQ+ people through retreats and advocacy. He also started Virtudent, the first national telehealth dentistry company. His work in health, policy, and community is rooted in early advocacy during his family‚Äôs immigration fight.
column14: Haley Everheart is the VP of Marketing at FOLX Health, a digital healthcare company focused on providing inclusive and affirming care for the LGBTQIA+ community. With experience in marketing and brand strategy, she leads the company's efforts to reach and engage individuals seeking specialized healthcare services. Everheart is passionate about building brands that authentically represent and advocate for marginalized communities. She previously held leadership roles at various consumer-focused companies, bringing a diverse background to her current position at FOLX Health. Her focus is on driving growth and awareness through impactful marketing campaigns.

column14: Madison Butler is a fiery advocate for workplace equity and inclusion, particularly focusing on creating spaces where marginalized individuals can thrive. As the Founder of Blue Haired Unicorn, she consults with organizations on building more inclusive cultures through actionable strategies. Known for her candid and often unconventional approach, Madison challenges the status quo and pushes for radical change in HR and leadership practices. Her work centers around dismantling systemic barriers and empowering individuals to advocate for themselves and others. She is a sought-after speaker and thought leader on topics such as psychological safety, anti-racism, and building inclusive teams.

column14: Dr. Hitesh Tolani is the founder of Gays of National Parks (GONP), a community dedicated to connecting LGBTQ+ individuals with nature and promoting inclusivity in the outdoors. He is a physician, specifically in the field of nephrology. Tolani created GONP to address the lack of representation and visibility for queer people in outdoor spaces. Through GONP, he organizes group trips and events, fostering a sense of belonging and encouraging exploration of national parks. His work aims to empower LGBTQ+ individuals to embrace nature and advocate for its conservation.

[Femigrants Foundation](https://lu.ma/calendar/cal-dzqYGfM3RP4Epkl)

Jun

2

6:00 PM - 8:30 PM PDT

[The Ameswell Hotel\\
\\
Mountain View, California](https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=The%20Ameswell%20Hotel&query_place_id=ChIJl6H4PES3j4ARhg_YFtINXiA)

Registration Closed

This event is not currently taking registrations. You may contact the host or subscribe to receive updates.

About Event

## ‚Äã5/22/2025 Update: Since 5/26 is a Labor Day long weekend, we are rescheduling this event to 6/2/2025 based on your requests.

‚Äãüìç **Ameswell Hotel, Mountain View, CA**

‚ÄãüìÖ **Monday, May 26, 2025** \| 6 PM - 8:30 PM

‚Äãü•ò **Food:** NOT included. Will be served per guest's order.

‚Äãüëî **Dress Code:** Summer colors!

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=1303/editor-images/kz/240865a9-cef6-412c-a95a-078a0a3ba691.jpg)

‚ÄãThis event is designed exclusively for **immigrant entrepreneurs and small to medium-sized business owners** who are working hard to grow their companies and businesses ‚Äîoften without the community support they truly need.

‚Äã **Seats of Success** is a call to **listen, collaborate, and co-create solutions**. Join us for an intimate and empowering gathering where your voice matters.

‚Äã **What to expect:**

- ‚Äã **Mastermind Circle:** Each attendee will introduce themselves and their business, and share specific areas where support is needed.

- ‚Äã **Fireside Chat:** Hear from a successful immigrant entrepreneur who scaled her business to **$1M in annual revenue**, sharing the real lessons behind her growth.


‚ÄãThis event aims to build bridges between immigrant entrepreneurs, the community, and organizations that want to support them.

‚ÄãLet‚Äôs uplift and invest in each other‚Äîbecause thriving immigrant businesses uplift entire communities.

‚ÄãMore exciting details will be announced shortly!

‚Äã\*Open to **ALL genders!**

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=533.3849728892332/editor-images/br/a83a3ad6-6cf8-4feb-903c-3b97d449b444.jpg)

‚Äã **WHO SHOULD JOIN?**

‚Äã **Immigrant entrepreneurs** who own or operate **small to medium businesses** and seek meaningful connections, tailored support, and **practical strategies for growth**.

‚Äã **WHY YOU SHOULD JOIN?**

- ‚ÄãEngage in an open, supportive dialogue to express your unique challenges and needs.

- ‚ÄãBenefit from targeted insights and feedback from fellow entrepreneurs and industry leaders.

- ‚ÄãHelp Femigrants Foundation identify specific services and support structures tailored to empower your business and expand your clientele.


‚Äã **FIRESIDE CHAT SPEAKER**

‚ÄãTo be announced soon!

‚Äã **DRESS CODE:**

‚Äã **Let's celebrate our unity in the spring colors of green or lavender and/or pink!**

‚Äã **MENU:**

‚Äã **Food and drinks are not included in the event ticket.** We will gather at the Ameswell Hotel which offers a great menu selection at the Rogers Restaurant. **_Guests are welcome to order directly from the menu at their own expense._**

‚Äã **LOCATION:**

‚ÄãAmeswell Hotel, venue details and instructions will be emailed to the registered guests a few days before the event

‚Äã **RESERVATION:**

‚ÄãP.S. We don't sell tickets at the door! Please register on Luma before joining the event.

‚Äã **The tickets are non-refundable.**

* * *

## ‚Äã **EVENT ORGANIZER**

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=954.8387096774194/editor-images/lj/27ce633f-e523-4d8f-8ca4-7568c2dfba38.jpg)

‚Äã‚ÄãThis event is organized by **[AYTAKIN ALIYEVA](https://www.linkedin.com/in/aytakin-aliyeva-femigrants/)** **,** Forbes and Business Insider Featured Community Builder and Founder of the [Femigrants Foundation](https://femigrants.com/).

‚ÄãAytakin is a **podcast host** of the " [Verso Talk with Aytakin](https://www.youtube.com/@VersoTalkwithAytakin)" and the **[LinkedIn Influencer](https://www.linkedin.com/in/aytakin-aliyeva-femigrants/)** **and Content Creator**.

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **_[Femigrants](https://femigrants.com/)_** **_(501c3) is a global community of diverse female immigrants in business and STEAM in Silicon Valley. We connect immigrant women to business and career growth resources through unique and memorable event experiences._**

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãAs the Founder of the Femigrants Foundation, Aytakin orchestrates exceptional event experiences in Silicon Valley, fostering meaningful connections among female immigrants from diverse backgrounds and equipping them with valuable career and business resources.

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãAytakin's impactful work as a community leader has earned her international recognition, including **double gold awards from the prestigious Women Changing The World Awards.** Additionally, she was honored as one of the **Top 25 Female Influencers of 2023 by WomElle**, solidifying her position as a trailblazer in her field.

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãHer compelling journey in cultivating the Femigrants community has garnered widespread attention, earning her media coverage in esteemed outlets such as **Forbes, Business Insider, Yahoo Finance (twice), AP News, Washington Post, Intuit, Huffmag, London Daily Post**, and more.

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãBesides leading the Femigrants Foundation, Aytakin worked at Fortune 500 Tech companies such as Instagram, Oculus, NVIDIA, and HTC VIVE, leading digital marketing and creative operations teams.

## ‚Äã **FEMIGRANTS FOUNDATION**

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=533.2860436247562/editor-images/4t/4de00e73-8001-4151-8975-09b46f8195eb.jpg)

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãFounded in 2017 by the immigrant founder, [Aytakin (Ika) Aliyeva](https://www.linkedin.com/in/aytakin-aliyeva-femigrants/), [Femigrants](https://femigrants.com/) is a **global community (501c3 non-profit) of diverse female immigrants in startups, investments, businesses, and tech**. At Femigrants, we connect immigrant leaders to business and career growth resources through unique events and training programs.

# Techstars San Francisco Spring 2025 Demo Day

[Techstars San Francisco](https://lu.ma/techstarssf?k=c)

May

29

Thursday, May 29

3:30 PM - 7:30 PM PDT

Register to See Address

San Francisco, California

Registration Closed

This event is not currently taking registrations. You may contact the host or subscribe to receive updates.

About Event

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãJoin us for **Techstars San Francisco Demo Day** and see our newest class of founders share the innovative companies they're building - featuring special live Q&As with our Entrepreneurs in Residence!

‚ÄãThese founders are building the next generation of AI vertical solutions for sales enablement, adtech, healthcare, legaltech and so much more. Join us in celebrating their progress over the last 3 months!

‚Äã‚ÄãTechstars San Francisco is proud to continue our partnership with the Google Cloud. This partnership gives early stage startups in Techstars programs access to a breadth of Google resources designed for early-stage startup founders unlock the full potential of Google Cloud, including its latest innovations in AI.‚Äã

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãAgenda:

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã3:30 pm: Doors open and networking

‚Äã‚Äã4:15 pm: LAST ENTRY

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã4:15 pm - 6:00 pm: Managing Director Remarks & Company Presentations

‚Äã‚Äã6:00 pm - 7:30 pm: Cocktail Networking Hour + Refreshments

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãWith any questions, please contact Chloe Lannert, Program Manager at Techstars San Francisco [chloe.lannert@techstars.com](mailto:chloe.lannert@techstars.com)

‚ÄãThank you to our brilliant GNPs!

column14: Chloe Lannert is a Program Manager at Techstars San Francisco, focusing on supporting and mentoring early-stage startups. She brings a strong background in operations and community building to her role. Lannert is dedicated to fostering a collaborative and supportive environment within the Techstars accelerator program. Her work involves facilitating workshops, connecting founders with relevant resources, and helping them navigate the challenges of scaling their businesses. She appears passionate about empowering entrepreneurs and contributing to the startup ecosystem.

# Techstars San Francisco Spring 2025 Demo Day

[Techstars San Francisco](https://lu.ma/techstarssf?k=c)

May

29

Thursday, May 29

3:30 PM - 7:30 PM PDT

Register to See Address

San Francisco, California

Registration Closed

This event is not currently taking registrations. You may contact the host or subscribe to receive updates.

About Event

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãJoin us for **Techstars San Francisco Demo Day** and see our newest class of founders share the innovative companies they're building - featuring special live Q&As with our Entrepreneurs in Residence!

‚ÄãThese founders are building the next generation of AI vertical solutions for sales enablement, adtech, healthcare, legaltech and so much more. Join us in celebrating their progress over the last 3 months!

‚Äã‚ÄãTechstars San Francisco is proud to continue our partnership with the Google Cloud. This partnership gives early stage startups in Techstars programs access to a breadth of Google resources designed for early-stage startup founders unlock the full potential of Google Cloud, including its latest innovations in AI.‚Äã

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãAgenda:

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã3:30 pm: Doors open and networking

‚Äã‚Äã4:15 pm: LAST ENTRY

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã4:15 pm - 6:00 pm: Managing Director Remarks & Company Presentations

‚Äã‚Äã6:00 pm - 7:30 pm: Cocktail Networking Hour + Refreshments

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãWith any questions, please contact Chloe Lannert, Program Manager at Techstars San Francisco [chloe.lannert@techstars.com](mailto:chloe.lannert@techstars.com)

‚ÄãThank you to our brilliant GNPs!

column14: Andrea Perdomo is a Director at Techstars San Francisco, where she focuses on investing in and supporting early-stage startups. Her background includes experience in venture capital and startup operations, bringing a diverse perspective to the accelerator program. She's particularly interested in companies building solutions in areas like fintech and enterprise software. Andrea is known for her dedication to helping founders navigate the challenges of building successful businesses. Her expertise and network are valuable assets to the startups she mentors at Techstars.

column14: Umar is a Managing Director at Techstars San Francisco, focusing on investing in and mentoring early-stage startups. He has a background in product and growth, previously working at companies like Opendoor and Google. Umar's expertise lies in helping startups navigate product development, market strategy, and scaling operations. He brings a strong operator's perspective to the Techstars program, guiding founders through the challenges of building a successful business. His investment interests are broad but often include areas like proptech, fintech, and consumer technology.

# ‚Äã Human Potential in the Age of AI

# ‚ÄãThe Human+Tech Summit (June 17-19), with over 100 Speakers and Thought Leaders, is the centerpiece of [Human+Tech Week](https://humantechweek.com/)

‚Äã _Connect with Human+Tech Speakers, Thought Leaders, and Attendees, and hear about all the amazing sessions and experiences you'll encounter ‚Äì before the Event! Our AI Event Docent, "Gobby," is available to chat (voice or text) ‚Äì No purchase required:_ _[https://humantechweek.com/gobby](https://humantechweek.com/gobby)_

## ‚Äã **HUMAN+TECH WEEK** is where **visionary founders, industry leaders, strategic investors,** and **pioneering scientists** **explore Human Potential in the Age of AI.**

## ‚Äã **VIP All-Access Purchasers receive access to Additional Exclusive Human+Tech Week Events, including:**

‚Äã **[Inflection AI AGI House Build Day](https://app.agihouse.org/events/hai-build-day-20250614?utm_source=HTSluma)** **on June 14th: Human+Tech Week kicks off at the storied** **[AGI House in Hillsborough](https://app.agihouse.org/events/hai-build-day-20250614?utm_source=HTSluma)** **! (Access limited to select builders and VIP ticket holders only.)**

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=183.57487922705312/editor-images/vh/12e40cd1-8a83-4a09-94ee-e5f0e5e90e1c.png)

‚Äã **Monday, June 16th, we're hosting an Exclusive** **[Human+Agents Co-Evolution Symposium](https://lu.ma/HA-CoEvo?utm_source=hts_luma)** **with** **[Barney Pell](https://www.linkedin.com/in/barneypell/)** **&** **[Nichol Bradford](https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholbradford/)** **. Available by invitation and to VIP ticket holders only, and supported by** **[Magic](https://getmagic.com/?utm_source=HTW)** **:**

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=281.8505338078292/editor-images/ux/5a72eb5f-a005-492f-8385-98d691e0e219.webp)

‚ÄãThere are many ways to participate with Human+Tech Week, including Sponsorships, Community Partners, Facilitators, Startup Demos, Media Provider, Volunteering, and even Attending. **[Just fill out our participation form.](https://humantechweek.com/form)**

**[Sponsorship opportunities are available here.](https://docsend.com/v/t2vsk/htw-partner-deck)**

## ‚ÄãFor Human+Tech Summit, we're curating three full-days of unprecedented offerings, including **Keynotes, Panels, Workshops, Exhibits, Installations, Facilitated Experiences, Roundtable Discussions**, and much more; all across a comprehensive multi-track agenda:

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=242.5/editor-images/p8/7d83140a-0b02-42e0-b771-d41657672964.jpg)

‚Äã **HUMAN+TECH WEEK** is housed at the beautiful and spacious **One Beach St.**, that features **expansive views of the San Francisco Bay**. We‚Äôre filling 3-floors and over 100,000 sq. ft. with incredible **Keynotes, Panels, Workshops, Exhibits, Installations, Facilitated Experiences, Roundtable Discussions**, and much, much more

‚Äã **HUMAN + TECH WEEK is the definitive gathering at the intersection of AI and human potential.**

‚Äã **We believe AI can unlock human capacity at scale‚Äîfueling unprecedented innovation and progress. Now is the time to focus on human thriving.**

‚Äã **There has never been a better time to build or invest in the preventative health, wellbeing, and performance companies that address some of the biggest, and most expensive, problems plaguing the world.**

‚Äã **Join visionary founders, leaders, innovators, and strategic investors. Connect with the brightest minds, experience breakthrough innovations, and amplify your impact through powerful networking and collaboration.**

‚Äã **Don‚Äôt just watch the future unfold‚Äîshape it with us at Human Tech Week**

## ‚Äã **About our Sponsors & Partners:**

‚Äã **[Inflection AI](https://inflection.ai/?utm_source=HTWluma)** **develops emotionally intelligent, enterprise-grade conversational AI. With a bedrock commitment to human-centered design, Inflection builds AI systems that communicate naturally, align with individual and organizational values, and support high-trust interactions. Their work combines cutting-edge research in emotional intelligence with scalable infrastructure to enhance enterprise communication, productivity, and decision-making ‚Äî augmenting human capability rather than replacing it.**

‚Äã **[Magic](https://getmagic.com/?utm_source=HTW)** **provides the next generation of executive assistants. Magic matches you with an executive assistant dedicated solely to you. Your assistant is from the top 0.5% of our talent pool and is super-powered with Magic AI:** **[getmagic.com](https://getmagic.com/?utm_source=HTW)**

**‚ÄúMagic 24/7‚Äù provides access to a team of trained assistants, on demand, whenever you need:** **[getmagic.com/magic-247](https://getmagic.com/magic-247/?utm_source=HTW)**

‚Äã **[Transformative Tech](https://transformativetech.org/)** **'s mission is to bring 1 billion people into a state of fundamental wellbeing by 2030 through the aggregated impact of their global community.**

**Transformative Tech** exists to educate, gather, and activate passionate people committed to building the next generation of transformative technologies that will redefine wellbeing for the next decade.

‚Äã **[Niremia Collective](https://www.niremia.vc/)** **partners with visionary startups, aligned investors, and TransformativeTech, the world's largest wellbeing tech ecosystem. The network offers unparalleled access to opportunities and insights, driving impactful innovation.**

column14: Nichol Bradford is the Founder and Executive Producer of the Willow Group, focused on creating transformative experiences through immersive media and technology. She is a leading voice in the field of leveraging technology for wellness and personal growth, particularly through virtual reality and other emerging platforms. Bradford previously served as CEO of Transformative Tech and has held executive positions in the gaming industry. Her work centers around harnessing technology's potential to improve human well-being and build a more connected, compassionate world. She advocates for ethical and responsible development in the tech space.

# ‚Äã Human Potential in the Age of AI

# ‚ÄãThe Human+Tech Summit (June 17-19), with over 100 Speakers and Thought Leaders, is the centerpiece of [Human+Tech Week](https://humantechweek.com/)

‚Äã _Connect with Human+Tech Speakers, Thought Leaders, and Attendees, and hear about all the amazing sessions and experiences you'll encounter ‚Äì before the Event! Our AI Event Docent, "Gobby," is available to chat (voice or text) ‚Äì No purchase required:_ _[https://humantechweek.com/gobby](https://humantechweek.com/gobby)_

## ‚Äã **HUMAN+TECH WEEK** is where **visionary founders, industry leaders, strategic investors,** and **pioneering scientists** **explore Human Potential in the Age of AI.**

## ‚Äã **VIP All-Access Purchasers receive access to Additional Exclusive Human+Tech Week Events, including:**

‚Äã **[Inflection AI AGI House Build Day](https://app.agihouse.org/events/hai-build-day-20250614?utm_source=HTSluma)** **on June 14th: Human+Tech Week kicks off at the storied** **[AGI House in Hillsborough](https://app.agihouse.org/events/hai-build-day-20250614?utm_source=HTSluma)** **! (Access limited to select builders and VIP ticket holders only.)**

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=183.57487922705312/editor-images/vh/12e40cd1-8a83-4a09-94ee-e5f0e5e90e1c.png)

‚Äã **Monday, June 16th, we're hosting an Exclusive** **[Human+Agents Co-Evolution Symposium](https://lu.ma/HA-CoEvo?utm_source=hts_luma)** **with** **[Barney Pell](https://www.linkedin.com/in/barneypell/)** **&** **[Nichol Bradford](https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholbradford/)** **. Available by invitation and to VIP ticket holders only, and supported by** **[Magic](https://getmagic.com/?utm_source=HTW)** **:**

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=281.8505338078292/editor-images/ux/5a72eb5f-a005-492f-8385-98d691e0e219.webp)

‚ÄãThere are many ways to participate with Human+Tech Week, including Sponsorships, Community Partners, Facilitators, Startup Demos, Media Provider, Volunteering, and even Attending. **[Just fill out our participation form.](https://humantechweek.com/form)**

**[Sponsorship opportunities are available here.](https://docsend.com/v/t2vsk/htw-partner-deck)**

## ‚ÄãFor Human+Tech Summit, we're curating three full-days of unprecedented offerings, including **Keynotes, Panels, Workshops, Exhibits, Installations, Facilitated Experiences, Roundtable Discussions**, and much more; all across a comprehensive multi-track agenda:

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=242.5/editor-images/p8/7d83140a-0b02-42e0-b771-d41657672964.jpg)

‚Äã **HUMAN+TECH WEEK** is housed at the beautiful and spacious **One Beach St.**, that features **expansive views of the San Francisco Bay**. We‚Äôre filling 3-floors and over 100,000 sq. ft. with incredible **Keynotes, Panels, Workshops, Exhibits, Installations, Facilitated Experiences, Roundtable Discussions**, and much, much more

‚Äã **HUMAN + TECH WEEK is the definitive gathering at the intersection of AI and human potential.**

‚Äã **We believe AI can unlock human capacity at scale‚Äîfueling unprecedented innovation and progress. Now is the time to focus on human thriving.**

‚Äã **There has never been a better time to build or invest in the preventative health, wellbeing, and performance companies that address some of the biggest, and most expensive, problems plaguing the world.**

‚Äã **Join visionary founders, leaders, innovators, and strategic investors. Connect with the brightest minds, experience breakthrough innovations, and amplify your impact through powerful networking and collaboration.**

‚Äã **Don‚Äôt just watch the future unfold‚Äîshape it with us at Human Tech Week**

## ‚Äã **About our Sponsors & Partners:**

‚Äã **[Inflection AI](https://inflection.ai/?utm_source=HTWluma)** **develops emotionally intelligent, enterprise-grade conversational AI. With a bedrock commitment to human-centered design, Inflection builds AI systems that communicate naturally, align with individual and organizational values, and support high-trust interactions. Their work combines cutting-edge research in emotional intelligence with scalable infrastructure to enhance enterprise communication, productivity, and decision-making ‚Äî augmenting human capability rather than replacing it.**

‚Äã **[Magic](https://getmagic.com/?utm_source=HTW)** **provides the next generation of executive assistants. Magic matches you with an executive assistant dedicated solely to you. Your assistant is from the top 0.5% of our talent pool and is super-powered with Magic AI:** **[getmagic.com](https://getmagic.com/?utm_source=HTW)**

**‚ÄúMagic 24/7‚Äù provides access to a team of trained assistants, on demand, whenever you need:** **[getmagic.com/magic-247](https://getmagic.com/magic-247/?utm_source=HTW)**

‚Äã **[Transformative Tech](https://transformativetech.org/)** **'s mission is to bring 1 billion people into a state of fundamental wellbeing by 2030 through the aggregated impact of their global community.**

**Transformative Tech** exists to educate, gather, and activate passionate people committed to building the next generation of transformative technologies that will redefine wellbeing for the next decade.

‚Äã **[Niremia Collective](https://www.niremia.vc/)** **partners with visionary startups, aligned investors, and TransformativeTech, the world's largest wellbeing tech ecosystem. The network offers unparalleled access to opportunities and insights, driving impactful innovation.**

‚Äã **[Aiify.io](http://aiify.io/)** **creates AI events for Humans: including creators, developers, integrators, businesses, designers, and other professionals exploring how AI can be leveraged for practical solutions and increased efficiency ‚Äì today and into the future.**

[CommunityKit](https://lu.ma/communitykit?k=c)

Jun

9

Monday, June 9

11:00 AM - Jun 11, 10:00 PM EDT

[10380 Perimeter Rd\\
\\
Cupertino, California](https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=10380%20Perimeter%20Rd&query_place_id=ChIJbZnNWpi1j4ARFo63FfwKZ2E)

Welcome! To join the event, please register below.

Register

You will be asked to verify token ownership with your wallet.

About Event

‚ÄãIf you're in town for WWDC25, you're welcome at CommunityKit ‚Äì we'll be hosting WWDC25 keynote & SOTU watch party, meetups, workshops, hackathons, and more, so that everyone can come and meet like-minded developers in the heart of Cupertino.

You can check out our site for the schedule: [https://communitykit.social/schedule.html](https://communitykit.social/schedule.html)

# ‚ÄãOur Goal

‚ÄãGet ready to make the most of your WWDC experience with CommunityKit, located at the intersection of innovation and celebration. From June 9 though 11, join us at the Hyatt House Cupertino to gather with your fellow participants, learn so many new things, and build some great memories.

‚ÄãEach day, we‚Äôll be joined by our wonderful communities, such as Shortcuts, and iOSDevHappyHour, to name a few. We'll also be hosting a live recording of Swift over Coffee, focusing on everything new at WWDC.

‚ÄãThe collaboration within the indie dev community is a prime example of how we build one another up, especially since we often have to be both developers and designers. We're thrilled to share that we're hosting slots for indies of all backgrounds to show off their current project. It could be an app, design, or anything in between.

‚ÄãAs you can see, we‚Äôve got a lot of fun and great experience planned this year, and we can‚Äôt wait for June to get here so we can all get together and put the Community in CommunityKit.

‚Äã

‚ÄãWe are proudly sponsored by RevenueCat

# üß† The Thought Experiment Lab \[public\]

Hosted by Mendel Liu & The SF Commons

Jun

4

Wednesday, June 4

6:30 PM - 8:00 PM PDT

[550 Laguna St\\
\\
San Francisco, California](https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=550%20Laguna%20St&query_place_id=ChIJQ9xlT6KAhYAReQIfVQZP4ds)

Welcome! To join the event, please register below.

Register

You will be asked to verify token ownership with your wallet.

About Event

‚ÄãNote: while there are many guests listed in the RSVP, most of these are carried over from previous events in this series. We don't expect much more than 30 to attend.

"Imagination without reason is mere fancy, but reason without imagination is sterile. That is partly why scientists and philosophers alike have always used imaginary scenarios to help sharpen their ideas and push them to their limits." - _The Pig that Wants to be Eaten_, by Julian Baggini

For this meeting (June 4), we'll be discussing poverty and inequality and their relation to moral justification. We'll consider questions such as:

- ‚ÄãIs it more important to consider the number of people in poverty, or the proportion of people in poverty?

- ‚ÄãIf overall outcomes increase even as inequality worsens, is this progress?

- ‚ÄãDoes historical disenfranchisement morally require modern remediation?

- ‚ÄãWhen does/doesn't progress justify existing policies?


- ‚ÄãWe'll take some time to review this primer on is vs ought: [https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-6dt0G5wYu-DhlCrLrF41FTLvgw24tK-/view?usp=drive\_link](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-6dt0G5wYu-DhlCrLrF41FTLvgw24tK-/view?usp=drive_link)

- ‚ÄãTo get a taste of what the discussion might be about, it is highly recommended to also read this short article beforehand: [https://people.brandeis.edu/~teuber/Pogge,%20World%20Poverty%20and%20Human%20Rights.pdf](https://people.brandeis.edu/~teuber/Pogge,%20World%20Poverty%20and%20Human%20Rights.pdf)


‚ÄãSome examples of things we've discussed at past meetings:

- ‚ÄãCould a vegetarian eat a pig with a clear conscience, if that pig wanted to be eaten?

- ‚ÄãDoes a person survive using a teleporter that destroys the body and recreates it with perfect fidelity?

- ‚ÄãDoes the existence of evil in the world pose a problem for belief in a benevolent God?


‚ÄãWe'll be meeting in the 550 Room (down the stairs on the North side). Contact me by text if you're having trouble finding the location.

‚ÄãOn the Wednesdays when we're not running this event, we'll often be having similar discussions here: [https://lu.ma/shortstories](https://lu.ma/shortstories)

column14: Johnny Chang is a Partner at Pear VC, a seed-stage venture capital firm. He hosts the Stanford Founders podcast, interviewing successful Stanford alumni entrepreneurs. Prior to Pear, he co-founded a YC-backed startup and gained experience at Facebook. He focuses on investing in early-stage companies, particularly those with strong technical founders. His background in engineering and entrepreneurship allows him to connect with founders on a deeper level.

column1: Stanford Founders Demo Day | Spring 2025
column2: The Stanford Founders Demo Day ‚Äì Spring 2025 is a premier gathering designed to foster innovation, showcase talent, and ignite meaningful connections within the Stanford entrepreneurial ecosystem.
column11: Connect with Johnny Chang to discuss the Stanford founder network and team dynamics. Talk to Sophie Ren about venture ecosystems, strategic investments, and building powerful partnerships. Learn from Chris Bradbury about startup participation, scaling strategies, and founder support. Get expert insights from Francesco Marchioni on Aero & Defense industry participation. Talk to Rohan Parekh about industry trends, innovations, and opportunities in energy and sustainability.

column14: Francesco Marchioni is a Lecturer at Stanford University's d.school, focusing on design thinking and entrepreneurship. He's the host of the Stanford Founders podcast, interviewing prominent Stanford entrepreneurs about their startup journeys. He previously worked at IDEO and has experience founding his own ventures. Marchioni is passionate about helping students and aspiring entrepreneurs develop innovative solutions and build successful companies. His expertise lies in translating design principles into actionable business strategies.

column1: Stanford Founders Demo Day | Spring 2025
column2: The Stanford Founders Demo Day ‚Äì Spring 2025 is a premier gathering designed to foster innovation, showcase talent, and ignite meaningful connections within the Stanford entrepreneurial ecosystem.
column11: Connect with Johnny Chang to discuss the Stanford founder network and team dynamics. Talk to Sophie Ren about venture ecosystems, strategic investments, and building powerful partnerships. Learn from Chris Bradbury about startup participation, scaling strategies, and founder support. Get expert insights from Francesco Marchioni on Aero & Defense industry participation. Talk to Rohan Parekh about industry trends, innovations, and opportunities in energy and sustainability.

column14: Rohan Parekh is the host of the Stanford Founders Podcast, where he interviews successful Stanford entrepreneurs about their journeys. He's deeply involved in the Stanford entrepreneurship ecosystem, focusing on supporting and connecting founders. His background includes experience in venture capital and technology, giving him a keen understanding of the startup landscape. Parekh uses his podcast platform to share valuable insights and strategies with aspiring and current founders, drawing from real-world experiences. He is passionate about fostering innovation and helping entrepreneurs build impactful companies.

column1: Stanford Founders Demo Day | Spring 2025
column2: The Stanford Founders Demo Day ‚Äì Spring 2025 is a premier gathering designed to foster innovation, showcase talent, and ignite meaningful connections within the Stanford entrepreneurial ecosystem.
column11: Connect with Johnny Chang to discuss the Stanford founder network and team dynamics. Talk to Sophie Ren about venture ecosystems, strategic investments, and building powerful partnerships. Learn from Chris Bradbury about startup participation, scaling strategies, and founder support. Get expert insights from Francesco Marchioni on Aero & Defense industry participation. Talk to Rohan Parekh about industry trends, innovations, and opportunities in energy and sustainability.

column14: Chris Bradbury is the host of the Stanford Founders podcast, focusing on deep dives into the origin stories of successful Stanford-affiliated startups. He's an accomplished entrepreneur and investor himself, with a background in building and scaling technology companies. Bradbury also teaches entrepreneurship at Stanford, sharing his practical experience and insights with aspiring founders. He leverages his network and experience to bring valuable perspectives to the podcast's audience, exploring key moments and lessons learned from the startup journey.

column1: Stanford Founders Demo Day | Spring 2025
column2: The Stanford Founders Demo Day ‚Äì Spring 2025 is a premier gathering designed to foster innovation, showcase talent, and ignite meaningful connections within the Stanford entrepreneurial ecosystem.
column11: Connect with Johnny Chang to discuss the Stanford founder network and team dynamics. Talk to Sophie Ren about venture ecosystems, strategic investments, and building powerful partnerships. Learn from Chris Bradbury about startup participation, scaling strategies, and founder support. Get expert insights from Francesco Marchioni on Aero & Defense industry participation. Talk to Rohan Parekh about industry trends, innovations, and opportunities in energy and sustainability.

column14: Sophie R is a host at Stanford Founders, dedicated to highlighting the journeys and insights of Stanford-affiliated entrepreneurs. Her role involves interviewing founders, facilitating discussions, and creating content around startup experiences. She's passionate about fostering a strong community within the Stanford entrepreneurship ecosystem. Sophie brings a sharp understanding of the startup landscape, often delving into the nuanced challenges and successes faced by founders. Her work aims to inspire and provide actionable knowledge for aspiring and current entrepreneurs.

column1: Stanford Founders Demo Day | Spring 2025
column2: The Stanford Founders Demo Day ‚Äì Spring 2025 is a premier gathering designed to foster innovation, showcase talent, and ignite meaningful connections within the Stanford entrepreneurial ecosystem.
column11: Connect with Johnny Chang to discuss the Stanford founder network and team dynamics. Talk to Sophie Ren about venture ecosystems, strategic investments, and building powerful partnerships. Learn from Chris Bradbury about startup participation, scaling strategies, and founder support. Get expert insights from Francesco Marchioni on Aero & Defense industry participation. Talk to Rohan Parekh about industry trends, innovations, and opportunities in energy and sustainability.

With a background in building and scaling companies across various industries, including consumer tech and e-commerce, she brings practical insights to her conversations. Prior to podcasting, she held leadership roles at growth-stage startups, focusing on operations, strategy, and business development. Her expertise lies in helping early-stage companies navigate the challenges of growth and achieve sustainable success. Trishia is passionate about empowering founders and amplifying their stories.

column1: MCP Hackathon w/ Featureform, Cased, & Ridge Ventures
column2: Join Featureform, Cased, and Ridge Ventures for a weekend of hands-on building with the Model Context Protocol (MCP), the emerging standard for connecting models to tools and data. You‚Äôll be building alongside other developers, researchers, and engineers, solving real problems using MCP. Whether you‚Äôre creating an MCP server, building an application on top, or experimenting with new ideas, this is your space to explore and ship. Expect lightning talks, technical deep dives, and casual discussions from some of the best minds in AI infrastructure. At the end of the weekend, you‚Äôll demo your work in front of a panel of top engineers, founders, and investors.
column11: Simba Khadder is the founder of Featureform.
column14: Simba Khadder is the founder of Featureform, a platform focused on simplifying and standardizing the creation, management, and deployment of machine learning features. Recognizing the complexities and inefficiencies in operationalizing machine learning models, he built Featureform to help data scientists and engineers collaborate more effectively. His work at Featureform addresses the critical need for reliable feature engineering and serving, particularly in real-time prediction scenarios. Khadder's background likely involves experience in data science and software engineering, informing his approach to building scalable and user-friendly tools for the ML lifecycle. Featureform reflects his vision of democratizing access to sophisticated feature engineering practices.

column14: Remy Messadene is a co-founder and the Chief Product Officer at Founden, a company focused on simplifying company formation and management, particularly for startups. He is also the host of the Founden podcast, exploring entrepreneurship and the startup ecosystem. Before Founden, Remy was deeply involved in building and scaling companies, developing a strong understanding of the challenges founders face. His focus is on creating user-friendly tools and resources that empower entrepreneurs to navigate the complexities of launching and growing their businesses. He is passionate about democratizing access to the necessary infrastructure for successful entrepreneurship.

column14: Khalid Altalib is the Co-Founder and Host of Founden, a podcast focused on interviewing early-stage startup founders. He has a background in finance and investing, previously working in venture capital and private equity. His experience helps him provide insightful questions and engage in meaningful discussions with his guests about their entrepreneurial journeys. Through Founden, Khalid aims to demystify the startup process and share valuable lessons learned from founders in the trenches. He's passionate about supporting and highlighting the next generation of innovators.

About Event

‚ÄãPlease join fellow students from the Bay Area for the launch of EDU Arena‚Äîa global student initiative exploring how AI is redefining the academic experience. From smart study aids to career-focused research tools, discover what‚Äôs possible when AI becomes part of your learning journey.

‚Äãüéì Featuring insights from Prof. Houman Homayoun (UC Davis) and Prof. Crista Lopes (UC Irvine)

‚Äãüõ†Ô∏è Preview the global EDU Arena roadmap‚Äîand see how you can shape what‚Äôs next

‚ÄãüìÖ May 31, 2025 \| üïí 11 AM - 1 PM PT

‚Äãüìç Silicon Valley ‚Äì exact location will be shared upon admission.

‚ÄãSeats are limited‚Äîsecure yours now!

‚ÄãProgram:

‚ÄãThis session will kick off with a welcome and introduction to **EDUArena** and its mission, followed by an overview of the platform, its unique features, and how it empowers students to learn, experiment, and contribute. Attendees will experience a live demo, explore AI internship opportunities with Turing, and learn about the student ambassador program. The event will also feature expert-led seminars on personalized learning and agentic AI, offering valuable insights for students.

‚Äã **About Turing**

‚ÄãTuring enables companies like OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, NVIDIA, Meta, and Microsoft to measure and improve their foundation model capabilities in areas like reasoning, coding, function calling, multimodality, frontier STEM knowledge, factuality, and safety. By leveraging a global talent pool of over 3 million rigorously vetted software developers, data scientists, and knowledge workers from 100+ countries, Turing delivers expert human data for Evals, SFT, RLHF, and DPO. Founded in 2018, Turing achieved unicorn status in 2021.

‚Äã~

[Learn More about Turing: AI data startup Turing triples revenue to $300 million](https://www.reuters.com/technology/artificial-intelligence/ai-data-startup-turing-triples-revenue-300-million-2025-01-28/) (Reuters)

column14: Houman Homayoun is a Professor in the Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering at UC Davis, specializing in hardware security and energy-efficient computing. His research focuses on developing novel techniques to protect integrated circuits from various threats, including hardware Trojans and side-channel attacks. He also explores the design of energy-efficient architectures for emerging applications like machine learning and neuromorphic computing. Prof. Homayoun has received numerous awards for his research contributions in the field. He actively collaborates with industry partners to translate his research findings into practical solutions.

About Event

‚ÄãPlease join fellow students from the Bay Area for the launch of EDU Arena‚Äîa global student initiative exploring how AI is redefining the academic experience. From smart study aids to career-focused research tools, discover what‚Äôs possible when AI becomes part of your learning journey.

‚Äãüéì Featuring insights from Prof. Houman Homayoun (UC Davis) and Prof. Crista Lopes (UC Irvine)

‚Äãüõ†Ô∏è Preview the global EDU Arena roadmap‚Äîand see how you can shape what‚Äôs next

‚ÄãüìÖ May 31, 2025 \| üïí 11 AM - 1 PM PT

‚Äãüìç Silicon Valley ‚Äì exact location will be shared upon admission.

‚ÄãSeats are limited‚Äîsecure yours now!

‚ÄãProgram:

‚ÄãThis session will kick off with a welcome and introduction to **EDUArena** and its mission, followed by an overview of the platform, its unique features, and how it empowers students to learn, experiment, and contribute. Attendees will experience a live demo, explore AI internship opportunities with Turing, and learn about the student ambassador program. The event will also feature expert-led seminars on personalized learning and agentic AI, offering valuable insights for students.

‚Äã **About Turing**

‚ÄãTuring enables companies like OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, NVIDIA, Meta, and Microsoft to measure and improve their foundation model capabilities in areas like reasoning, coding, function calling, multimodality, frontier STEM knowledge, factuality, and safety. By leveraging a global talent pool of over 3 million rigorously vetted software developers, data scientists, and knowledge workers from 100+ countries, Turing delivers expert human data for Evals, SFT, RLHF, and DPO. Founded in 2018, Turing achieved unicorn status in 2021.

‚Äã~

[Learn More about Turing: AI data startup Turing triples revenue to $300 million](https://www.reuters.com/technology/artificial-intelligence/ai-data-startup-turing-triples-revenue-300-million-2025-01-28/) (Reuters)

column14: Crista Lopes is a Professor of Informatics at the University of California, Irvine, known for her research in programming languages, software engineering, and distributed systems. Her work explores innovative programming paradigms, particularly aspect-oriented programming and generative programming. She also investigates the design and architecture of large-scale distributed systems, including virtual worlds and social media platforms. Recently, she's been focusing on urban informatics and the impact of technology on urban environments. Her research aims to improve software development practices and create more resilient and sustainable technological systems.

column14: Max Gerber is a Tech Lead at Stytch, focusing on AI Agents and the development of infrastructure enabling AI capabilities. He is passionate about exploring the potential of AI to enhance user authentication and developer experiences. Prior to Stytch, Max worked on infrastructure and security engineering at companies like Opendoor and Palantir. His expertise lies in building scalable and reliable systems to support complex AI applications. He is a strong advocate for responsible AI development and its ethical implications.

column14: Dexter Horthy is the Founder and CEO of HumanLayer, a company focused on leveraging data and AI to improve employee experience and organizational performance. He is a thought leader in the field of people analytics and the future of work. Horthy has a background in building and scaling technology companies, with a particular emphasis on data-driven solutions. He is passionate about creating human-centric workplaces where employees can thrive. Under his leadership, HumanLayer aims to empower organizations with actionable insights to optimize their workforce.

column14: Johnathan McGowan is the Founder and CEO of PayOS, a unified commerce platform designed for retailers. He is an entrepreneur focused on simplifying omnichannel retail operations. McGowan's vision for PayOS stems from his experience in the retail technology space, recognizing the need for a more integrated and accessible solution. He is dedicated to empowering merchants with tools that streamline their business and enhance customer experiences. Under his leadership, PayOS aims to unify online and offline channels, enabling retailers to manage inventory, sales, and customer data in one place.

column14: Siddhant Mohan is a co-founder of Qodex.ai, a company focused on simplifying and democratizing AI adoption. He possesses a strong background in engineering and entrepreneurship, leveraging his expertise to develop AI solutions for various industries. His work centers around making complex AI technologies accessible and user-friendly, aiming to bridge the gap between AI research and practical business applications. He's dedicated to empowering businesses to harness the potential of AI to improve efficiency and innovation. He is a builder and problem-solver at heart.

column14: Abi Raghuram is the CTO of Codeintegrity.ai, a company focused on leveraging AI to enhance software security. He is a seasoned technologist with extensive experience in cloud computing, cybersecurity, and software development. At Codeintegrity.ai, Raghuram leads the technological vision and oversees the development of their AI-powered security solutions. His work revolves around identifying and mitigating vulnerabilities in code before they can be exploited. Raghuram is passionate about building innovative technologies that improve the trustworthiness of software.

column14: Kimi Kong is a co-founder of Energent AI, a company focused on developing AI solutions for energy and environmental challenges. Her background is in engineering and data science. She is passionate about leveraging AI to create a more sustainable and efficient future for the energy industry. At Energent AI, she focuses on product development and strategy, ensuring their AI technologies address critical needs in areas like grid optimization and carbon reduction. Kimi is committed to innovation and driving real-world impact through AI.

column14: Lisa N. Cao is a Product Manager at Datastrato, focusing on simplifying data governance and access. She's deeply involved in the Apache Gravitino project, where she contributes to its design and roadmap. Her work revolves around building open-source solutions that address the challenges of modern data ecosystems, ensuring data is discoverable, secure, and properly managed across diverse sources. Lisa is passionate about empowering data users and enabling organizations to effectively leverage their data assets. She brings her product management expertise to the open-source community to further innovate in data governance.

Through Structured Labs, she aims to empower organizations to make data-driven decisions more efficiently.

‚ÄãWe're excited to bring you an amazing roster of speakers with fantastic teams working on cutting-edge technology in Data & AI **Event Highlights:**

- ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **Networking Opportunities:** Connect with like-minded professionals who share your passion for AI and data.

- ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **Expert Talks:** Gain insights from industry leaders and pioneers in the field.

- ‚Äã [Harmeen Mehta](https://www.linkedin.com/in/harmeenm), Chief Digital and Innovation Officer @ [Equinix](https://www.linkedin.com/company/equinix), delivering opening remarks.

- ‚Äã [Lisa N. Cao](https://www.linkedin.com/in/lisancao/), Product Manager of [Apache Gravitino](https://gravitino.apache.org/) @ [Datastrato](https://www.linkedin.com/company/datastrato)

- ‚Äã [Amrutha Gujjar](https://www.linkedin.com/in/amruthagujjar/), CEO & Co-founder @ [Structured Labs](https://www.linkedin.com/company/structuredlabs) - _"Building data apps with AI: From Prototype to Production"_

- ‚Äã **[Jan ƒåurn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/jancurn/)**, CEO & Founder @ [Apify](https://www.linkedin.com/company/apifytech)\- _"Turbocharge your AI agents with 4,000 Actors"_

- ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **Innovative Ideas:** Discover new approaches and technologies that are shaping the future of AI.

column14: Jan ƒåurn is the CEO and founder of Apify, a web scraping and automation platform. He transitioned from a background in physics and software engineering to address the growing need for structured web data. Under his leadership, Apify has become a prominent player in the data extraction and automation space, empowering developers and businesses to leverage web data for various applications. His vision focuses on making web data accessible and actionable for everyone, regardless of technical expertise. ƒåurn's entrepreneurial drive stems from a passion for solving complex problems through innovative technology.

[All Things Web](https://lu.ma/allthingsweb?k=c)

May

28

Wednesday, May 28

5:00 PM - 8:00 PM PDT

[Vapi Inc.\\
\\
San Francisco, California](https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Vapi%20Inc.&query_place_id=ChIJtzdHQ3iBhYARuvjoXoECLW0)

Welcome! To join the event, please register below.

Register

You will be asked to verify token ownership with your wallet.

About Event

‚ÄãWhat‚Äôs new in Voice? A lot. LLMs are transforming the Voice AI space - and fast, too! Join us on May 28 at Vapi HQ in SF for an evening of cutting-edge tech talks, tasty snacks & drinks, and great conversations about the future of the web and Voice AI. Don‚Äôt miss it!

# ‚Äã‚ÄãTalks

- ‚Äã **Performance optimizing agent for Next.js**

_Lee Robinson,_ DX at Vercel

- ‚Äã **How I built an open source gemini live with Vapi**

_Elizabeth Trykin, DevRel at Vapi_

- ‚Äã **Giving your voice agents superpowers with MCP**

_Dan Goosewin, SDE Manager at Deaglo_


# ‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãSchedule

- ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **5:00 ‚Äì 6:00 PM**: Doors open! Grab a snack, enjoy a drink, and meet fellow attendees.

- ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **6:00 ‚Äì 7:00 PM**: Time for tech talks!

- ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **7:00 ‚Äì 8:00 PM**: Stick around to chat, connect, and dive deeper into all things web discussions.‚Äã


# ‚ÄãVapi Office Hours

‚ÄãA couple of Vapi engineers will be available from 7-8pm to help with support or to answer technical questions .

# ‚ÄãAbout Vapi

‚ÄãThis event is hosted by our friends at Vapi. Vapi is a developer platform for building, testing, and deploying voice AI agents. It provides the infrastructure for businesses and developers to create custom voice assistants that can handle call operations for existing customer support, appointment booking, and sales calls, or for building new products using voice AI like prior authorization and product onboarding assistants. Try Vapi at [vapi.ai](https://vapi.ai/).

# ‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãAbout All Things Web‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãWe are a group of web enthusiasts who love to bring the community together and chat about all things web! Subscribe to [our Luma calendar](https://lu.ma/allthingsweb) for upcoming events, visit [allthingsweb.dev](http://allthingsweb.dev/) to learn more, and [join our Discord](https://discord.gg/B3Sm4b5mfD) server to stay connected.

column14: Lee Robinson is a Vice President of Developer Experience (DX) at Vercel. He's known for his expertise in front-end web development, particularly with React, Next.js, and serverless technologies. He frequently speaks and writes about best practices in modern web architecture, focusing on performance and developer productivity. His work centers around making web development accessible and enjoyable for developers. Prior to Vercel, he worked in similar roles focusing on developer experience and education.

# Navy SEAL - Day in a Life Bootcamp

[Nova: Gargi's Events](https://lu.ma/nova-community?k=c)

May

31

Saturday, May 31

6:00 AM - 12:30 PM PDT

[Aquatic Park Bleachers\\
\\
San Francisco, California](https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Aquatic%20Park%20Bleachers&query_place_id=ChIJU3cpj-CAhYAR7FfD4Qq9xyc)

Welcome! Please choose your desired ticket type:

Get Ticket

You will be asked to verify token ownership with your wallet.

About Event

## ‚Äã  Do you have what it takes to train with a US navy SEAL?

## ‚ÄãThe Day In The Life of a Navy SEAL Event is a transformational experience designed for men and women who want to shatter their limits and redefine what they're capable of.

‚Äã

Participants will set new thresholds for pain, resilience, discipline and inner strength.

We only use 50-60% of our potential. Sometimes we need to be reminded how far we can push ourselves. Join us to stretch and be reminded of your full potential.

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=285.09316770186336/editor-images/z9/f0a48bd3-c2dc-454a-9570-c94841bcf4c1.png)

## ‚ÄãWho is this for

- ‚ÄãIf you've built success but still feel stuck - mentally, physically or emotionally

- ‚ÄãIf you're craving the kind of challenge that pushes beyond your comfort zone

- ‚ÄãIf you want to break through personal barriers and build unshakeable resilience

- ‚ÄãIf you're ready to find out what you're truly capable of

- ‚ÄãIf you're seeking transformation through discomfort, attention to detail, and grit.


## ‚ÄãTrain with One of The Few :

‚ÄãOut of approximately 14,000 Navy SEALs in history, only a select few have the experience and leadership to guide others through transformation. [Alex Rogers](https://www.linkedin.com/in/alex-rogers1/) is one of them. A former Special Warfare Operator First Class (SO1), Alex served 12 years with SEAL Team 3 completing deployments to Iraq and The UAE.

‚Äã

## ‚ÄãThis isn't a Seminar. It's a Test.

‚ÄãThis experience is unlike any business event, sales training or networking event you've been to. It's about confronting discomfort, embracing discipline and discovering what you're truly capable of. You'll either breakthrough - or quit.

‚ÄãIf you make it through, you'll meet a version of yourself you've never seen before.

## ‚ÄãWhy We Created This

‚ÄãIn a world filled with meetups, events and seminars, we wanted to offer something different, something more immersive.

‚ÄãWhile therapy and psychedelics have their place, physical challenges remain one of the most direct paths to overcoming mental and emotional barriers. This event is designed to push you beyond your limits to help you build resilience from the inside out.

## ‚ÄãWhat To Expect

- ‚ÄãImmersive Training: Live the routines and disciplines of a Navy SEAL

- ‚ÄãLeadership Insights : Learn how Alex applies SEAL principles to business, family and fitness.

- ‚ÄãPhysical Challenge : Engage in activities that test your endurance and mental fortitude.

- ‚ÄãPersonal Feedback : Get direct feedback that you'll take to break through barriers and discover your true potential.


## ‚ÄãYour Mission

‚ÄãJoin us for this one-of-a-kind event. Learn from the best. Push yourself beyond what you thought possible. Transform your life.

‚ÄãNo minimum fitness level required. This is an individual test. Learn how US Navy SEALS train so they can be pushed to 20X what they thought was possible. Your max is inconceivable. You need to test yourself to find out what that is.

## ‚ÄãMeet Alex Rogers: Former Navy SEAL & Leadership Coach

‚Äã [Alex Rogers](https://www.linkedin.com/in/alex-rogers1/) is a former U.S. Navy SEAL who served nearly 12 years, including deployments with SEAL Team THREE, one of the Navy‚Äôs most elite and storied special operations units. SEAL Team THREE is renowned for its rigorous selection process, distinguished history and are among the most highly trained and capable special operators in the world.

‚ÄãThroughout his distinguished military career, Alex was recognized with several prestigious awards:

- ‚Äã **Navy and Marine Corps Commendation Medal:** Awarded for meritorious achievement or service above and beyond the normal expectations of duty.

- ‚Äã **Joint Service Achievement Medal:** Presented for outstanding achievement or meritorious service while assigned to a joint activity, clearly placing the individual‚Äôs performance above that of contemporaries.

- ‚Äã **Navy and Marine Corps Achievement Medal with ‚ÄúC‚Äù Device:** Recognizes meritorious service or achievement under combat conditions, performed while exposed to hostile action or significant risk.

- ‚Äã **Combat Action Ribbon:** Awarded to Navy and Marine Corps personnel who render satisfactory performance under enemy fire while actively participating in a ground or surface engagement.


‚ÄãAfter concluding his military service in 2025, Alex transitioned into [leadership coachin](https://lfwcc.com/coaching/pay-as-you-go-online-coaching/) [g](https://lfwcc.com/cool-stuff/resilience-mastery-coaching-package/) and founded SEALFORCE, a program dedicated to helping individuals unlock their inner resilience and achieve levels of toughness they never thought possible. Alex brings a unique perspective on resilience, team dynamics, and performing under pressure to his [coaching practice](https://lfwcc.com/cool-stuff/resilience-mastery-coaching-package/).

‚ÄãOutside of his professional endeavors, Alex is a dedicated father and enjoys spending quality time with his children.

## ‚Äã  What to bring :

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=800/editor-images/0b/dc3a9beb-d637-4c2b-b6a7-885349dc7306.jpg)

- ‚ÄãWater

- ‚ÄãTowels

- ‚ÄãUniform : White Shirt (optional [Ready For Anything](https://lfwcc.com/coaching/) shirt), Black Shorts (Women - Shorts or Leggings)

- ‚Äã1 Extra Pair of Shoes


‚ÄãMedical Staff will be on site.

column14: Alex Rogers is a former Navy SEAL who served for over a decade, participating in multiple deployments and leading teams in high-pressure environments. He's recognized for his expertise in leadership, teamwork, and resilience, developed through his extensive military experience. After leaving the SEALs, Alex transitioned to coaching and consulting, focusing on applying his unique skillset to the corporate world. He helps organizations and individuals enhance their leadership capabilities, improve team performance, and develop mental fortitude. Rogers draws on real-world scenarios and actionable strategies to inspire and empower others to achieve peak performance.

column11: Dr. Garrett Vygantas: Venture investor, CEO, serial entrepreneur. Garrett Vygantas, MD, MBA is Founder & Managing Partner of Riverine Ventures, a life science and healthcare dedicated venture capital firm. Trained as a physician and an experienced entrepreneur, Garrett provides strategic direction and valuable clinical and commercial networks as a Board Member or Advisor to Adventris Pharma, AEye Health, ArtiSight, CellFE, Ceria Therapeutics, Corsair Pharma, Eliksa Therapeutics, HealthBridge, Inflammatix, KeifeRx, Mediphage and Pieces Technologies. With over 20 years, Garrett‚Äôs expertise spans across biopharma, life sciences, healthcare, medtech and digital health investing and operations. Before founding Riverine Ventures, he has invested on behalf of The 4100 Group, OSF Healthcare, Jump Capital and Burrill & Co. As an operator, he served as Founding CEO of TherOptix, NewBridge Pharmaceuticals and Mitre Medical and Chief Business Officer of Corsair Pharma. At NewBridge, he and his team raised over $60M in financing and created $470M in nominal value. Dr. Alex Colville: Investor in Longevity. Dr. Alex Colville is the General Partner and cofounder of age1 alongside Laura Deming. age1 is the continuation of the first longevity-focused VC fund founded in 2011 by Laura (5 IPOs). Alex is an advisor and previously served as founding Chief of Staff of the Amaranth Foundation, a family office dedicated to advancing interventions to extend healthy human lifespan where he led investments into over 20 companies and supported philanthropic initiatives including AFAR and the TIME Initiative. Prior to working for family offices, Alex received a PhD in genetics at Stanford University studying rejuvenation and the biology of aging in Tom Rando's lab. During his PhD he consulted for the business development group at Maze Therapeutics and the scientific team at Rubedo Life Sciences. Dr. Christin Glorioso: CEO & Co-founder, NeuroAge Therapeutics | Founder & Executive Director, Longevity Global. Dr. Christin Glorioso is a neuroscientist, physician, and serial entrepreneur. She is co-founder and CEO of NeuroAge Therapeutics and Founder and Executive Director of the non-profit, Longevity Global. Christin completed her postdoctoral training at MIT and holds an MD and PhD in Neuroscience from the University of Pittsburgh School of Medicine. Dr. Kazu Okuda: Kazu Okuda, M.D. is a physician turned neuro‚Äëtechnology entrepreneur driven to improve mental health care. Previously, he was involved in clinical development, fundraising, and ultimately securing regulatory clearance and national insurance reimbursement for an AI-powered medical device at a Japanese med-tech startup. He then moved to the United States to found Universal Brain in 2022, tackling a fundamental gap in psychiatry: the routine measurement of brain function. Universal Brain‚Äôs platform captures well-validated brain function measures, called event-related potentials (ERPs), that reflect core neural processes linked to depression and its treatment. By turning these EEG‚Äëbased measures into a scalable, clinic‚Äëready tool, he aims to make objective brain‚Äëfunction testing a standard component of mental‚Äëhealth care to get better outcomes‚Äîstarting with depression and expanding across psychiatric conditions. Allison M. Leopold Tilley: Partner at Pillsbury Winthrop Shaw Pittman LLP. Allison Leopold Tilley is named one of the top ‚ÄúWomen Leaders in Tech Law‚Äù by The Recorder for six consecutive years and hailed as the Technology ‚ÄúDealmaker of the Year‚Äù by The Deal. Based in Silicon Valley, Allison advises technology companies, including on their formation, venture capital financings, multibillion-dollar M&As, public offerings, securities transactions, SPAC transactions and board governance.

About Event

‚Äã **About Event**

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãIn a world driven by rapid and complex challenges, innovation thrives at the¬†**convergence**¬†of technologies.

‚Äã‚ÄãBy bringing together experts from different domain areas, we unlock new possibilities.

‚Äã‚ÄãWelcome to¬†**_DaVinci Caf√©_**, where thinkers, creators, and visionaries connect and collaborate.

‚Äã‚Äã **üóìÔ∏è¬†Agenda**

‚Äã‚Äã **Date: June 4th**

‚Äã‚Äã **Address:** 2550 Hanover Street \| Palo Alto, CA 94304-1115

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **5:00 PM**: check in & networking

**5:30-6:30 PM**: Panel discussion + Q&A

**6:30-7:00 PM**: networking üçïüç∫

‚Äã‚ÄãThis event will include light appetizers, wine/beer and non-alcoholic beverages.

‚Äã‚Äã **üéôÔ∏è¬†Our speakers**

‚ÄãModerator

‚ÄãDr. Garrett Vygantas: Venture investor, CEO, serial entrepreneur.

‚Äã

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=800/editor-images/pq/7e7535ac-3479-4276-b9ca-be23dc6e50e0.jpg)

‚ÄãGarrett Vygantas, MD, MBA is Founder & Managing Partner of Riverine Ventures, a life science and healthcare dedicated venture capital firm. Trained as a physician and an experienced entrepreneur, Garrett provides strategic direction and valuable clinical and commercial networks as a Board Member or Advisor to Adventris Pharma, AEye Health, ArtiSight, CellFE, Ceria Therapeutics, Corsair Pharma, Eliksa Therapeutics, HealthBridge, Inflammatix, KeifeRx, Mediphage and Pieces Technologies.

‚ÄãWith over 20 years, Garrett‚Äôs expertise spans across biopharma, life sciences, healthcare, medtech and digital health investing and operations. Before founding Riverine Ventures, he has invested on behalf of The 4100 Group, OSF Healthcare, Jump Capital and Burrill & Co. As an operator, he served as Founding CEO of TherOptix, NewBridge Pharmaceuticals and Mitre Medical and Chief Business Officer of Corsair Pharma. At NewBridge, he and his team raised over $60M in financing and created $470M in nominal value.

‚ÄãPanel speakers:

‚Äã1.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Dr. Alex Colville: Investor in Longevity

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=1200/editor-images/r1/f35b4680-1061-49d9-ad7e-360c5a835f42.jpg)

‚ÄãDr. Alex Colville is the General Partner and cofounder of age1 alongside Laura Deming. age1 is the continuation of the first longevity-focused VC fund founded in 2011 by Laura (5 IPOs). Alex is an advisor and previously served as founding Chief of Staff of the Amaranth Foundation, a family office dedicated to advancing interventions to extend healthy human lifespan where he led investments into over 20 companies and supported philanthropic initiatives including AFAR and the TIME Initiative. Prior to working for family offices, Alex received a PhD in genetics at Stanford University studying rejuvenation and the biology of aging in Tom Rando's lab. During his PhD he consulted for the business development group at Maze Therapeutics and the scientific team at Rubedo Life Sciences.

‚Äã2.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Dr. Christin Glorioso: CEO & Co-founder, NeuroAge Therapeutics \| Founder & Executive Director, Longevity Global

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=800/editor-images/ho/a00a13ba-cca5-4ac9-8163-e815e628273e.png)

‚ÄãDr. Christin Glorioso is a neuroscientist, physician, and serial entrepreneur.¬† She is co-founder and CEO of NeuroAge Therapeutics and Founder and Executive Director of the non-profit, Longevity Global. Christin completed her postdoctoral training at MIT and holds an MD and PhD in Neuroscience from the University of Pittsburgh School of Medicine.

‚Äã3\. Dr. Kazu Okuda

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=800/editor-images/rc/b65514a5-3d5d-4c91-9c62-2d8b357b58c3.jpg)

‚ÄãKazu¬†Okuda,¬†M.D. is a physician turned neuro‚Äëtechnology entrepreneur driven to improve mental health care. Previously, he was involved in clinical development, fundraising, and ultimately securing regulatory clearance and national insurance reimbursement for an AI-powered medical device at a Japanese med-tech startup. He then moved to the United States to found Universal¬†Brain in 2022, tackling a fundamental gap in psychiatry: the routine measurement of brain function.Universal¬†Brain‚Äôs platform captures well-validated brain function measures, called event-related potentials (ERPs), that reflect core neural processes linked to depression and its treatment. By turning these EEG‚Äëbased measures into a scalable, clinic‚Äëready tool, he aims to make objective brain‚Äëfunction testing a standard component of mental‚Äëhealth care to get better outcomes‚Äîstarting with depression and expanding across psychiatric conditions.

‚Äã4\. **[Allison M. Leopold Tilley](https://www.linkedin.com/in/allison-leopold-tilley/)** Partner at Pillsbury Winthrop Shaw Pittman LLP

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=1200/editor-images/1y/4b3fcbc0-9b45-473a-9679-8cbb4e496148.webp)

‚Äã‚Äã **Allison Leopold Tilley is named one of the top ‚ÄúWomen Leaders in Tech Law‚Äù by** **_The Recorder_** **for six consecutive years and hailed as the Technology ‚ÄúDealmaker of the Year‚Äù by** **_The Deal._** **Based in Silicon Valley, Allison advises technology companies, including on their formation, venture capital financings, multibillion-dollar M&As, public offerings, securities transactions, SPAC transactions and board governance.**

‚Äã **About the hosts & sponsors:**

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãHosts: Davinci Cafe: Where thinkers, creators, and visionaries from every industry connect, collaborate, and shape the future. Find your tribe, your partners, and your inspiration.

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãSponsors: Pillsbury Winthrop Shaw Pittman LLP: ‚Äã‚ÄãA global law firm focusing on the Tech, Energy, Financial, Real Estate & Construction, and Life Sciences industries.

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã _Please note, this event may be photographed and filmed. Davinci Cafe reserves the right to use photographs and video from the event for marketing and communications purposes. By attending the event you consent to your image being used for these purposes._

‚ÄãPanel speakers:

‚Äã1.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Dr. Alex Colville: Investor in Longevity

column14: Dr. Christin Glorioso is the CEO and co-founder of NeuroAge Therapeutics, a company focused on developing therapies to combat age-related neurodegenerative diseases like Alzheimer's. She holds a PhD in neuroscience and leverages her expertise in aging biology and drug development to advance novel therapeutic strategies. Her work centers on restoring healthy brain function by targeting the underlying mechanisms of aging. Dr. Glorioso is committed to translating scientific discoveries into clinically relevant treatments to improve cognitive healthspan. Her leadership drives NeuroAge's mission to extend the healthy lifespan of individuals at risk of or affected by neurodegenerative conditions.

column14: Dr. Kazu Okuda is the Founder of Universal Brain, a company focused on brain health optimization and performance enhancement. His expertise lies in applying neuroscience and artificial intelligence to personalized brain training programs. Prior to Universal Brain, Dr. Okuda held research positions at esteemed institutions, contributing to our understanding of cognitive function and neuroplasticity. His work emphasizes leveraging technology to improve cognitive abilities and promote healthy aging. He's driven by a passion for translating cutting-edge research into practical solutions that benefit individuals seeking to unlock their brain's full potential.

By turning these EEG‚Äëbased measures into a scalable, clinic‚Äëready tool, he aims to make objective brain‚Äëfunction testing a standard component of mental‚Äëhealth care to get better outcomes‚Äîstarting with depression and expanding across psychiatric conditions. Allison M. Leopold Tilley: Partner at Pillsbury Winthrop Shaw Pittman LLP. Allison Leopold Tilley is named one of the top ‚ÄúWomen Leaders in Tech Law‚Äù by The Recorder for six consecutive years and hailed as the Technology ‚ÄúDealmaker of the Year‚Äù by The Deal. Based in Silicon Valley, Allison advises technology companies, including on their formation, venture capital financings, multibillion-dollar M&As, public offerings, securities transactions, SPAC transactions and board governance.
