About Event

‚Äã **About Event**

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãIn a world driven by rapid and complex challenges, innovation thrives at the¬†**convergence**¬†of technologies.

‚Äã‚ÄãBy bringing together experts from different domain areas, we unlock new possibilities.

‚Äã‚ÄãWelcome to¬†**_DaVinci Caf√©_**, where thinkers, creators, and visionaries connect and collaborate.

‚Äã‚Äã **üóìÔ∏è¬†Agenda**

‚Äã‚Äã **Date: June 4th**

‚Äã‚Äã **Address:** 2550 Hanover Street \| Palo Alto, CA 94304-1115

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **5:00 PM**: check in & networking

**5:30-6:30 PM**: Panel discussion + Q&A

**6:30-7:00 PM**: networking üçïüç∫

‚Äã‚ÄãThis event will include light appetizers, wine/beer and non-alcoholic beverages.

‚Äã‚Äã **üéôÔ∏è¬†Our speakers**

‚ÄãModerator

‚ÄãDr. Garrett Vygantas: Venture investor, CEO, serial entrepreneur.

‚Äã

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=800/editor-images/pq/7e7535ac-3479-4276-b9ca-be23dc6e50e0.jpg)

‚ÄãGarrett Vygantas, MD, MBA is Founder & Managing Partner of Riverine Ventures, a life science and healthcare dedicated venture capital firm. Trained as a physician and an experienced entrepreneur, Garrett provides strategic direction and valuable clinical and commercial networks as a Board Member or Advisor to Adventris Pharma, AEye Health, ArtiSight, CellFE, Ceria Therapeutics, Corsair Pharma, Eliksa Therapeutics, HealthBridge, Inflammatix, KeifeRx, Mediphage and Pieces Technologies.

‚ÄãWith over 20 years, Garrett‚Äôs expertise spans across biopharma, life sciences, healthcare, medtech and digital health investing and operations. Before founding Riverine Ventures, he has invested on behalf of The 4100 Group, OSF Healthcare, Jump Capital and Burrill & Co. As an operator, he served as Founding CEO of TherOptix, NewBridge Pharmaceuticals and Mitre Medical and Chief Business Officer of Corsair Pharma. At NewBridge, he and his team raised over $60M in financing and created $470M in nominal value.

‚ÄãPanel speakers:

‚Äã1.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Dr. Alex Colville: Investor in Longevity

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=1200/editor-images/r1/f35b4680-1061-49d9-ad7e-360c5a835f42.jpg)

‚ÄãDr. Alex Colville is the General Partner and cofounder of age1 alongside Laura Deming. age1 is the continuation of the first longevity-focused VC fund founded in 2011 by Laura (5 IPOs). Alex is an advisor and previously served as founding Chief of Staff of the Amaranth Foundation, a family office dedicated to advancing interventions to extend healthy human lifespan where he led investments into over 20 companies and supported philanthropic initiatives including AFAR and the TIME Initiative. Prior to working for family offices, Alex received a PhD in genetics at Stanford University studying rejuvenation and the biology of aging in Tom Rando's lab. During his PhD he consulted for the business development group at Maze Therapeutics and the scientific team at Rubedo Life Sciences.

‚Äã2.¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† Dr. Christin Glorioso: CEO & Co-founder, NeuroAge Therapeutics \| Founder & Executive Director, Longevity Global

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=800/editor-images/ho/a00a13ba-cca5-4ac9-8163-e815e628273e.png)

‚ÄãDr. Christin Glorioso is a neuroscientist, physician, and serial entrepreneur.¬† She is co-founder and CEO of NeuroAge Therapeutics and Founder and Executive Director of the non-profit, Longevity Global. Christin completed her postdoctoral training at MIT and holds an MD and PhD in Neuroscience from the University of Pittsburgh School of Medicine.

‚Äã3\. Dr. Kazu Okuda

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=800/editor-images/rc/b65514a5-3d5d-4c91-9c62-2d8b357b58c3.jpg)

‚ÄãKazu¬†Okuda,¬†M.D. is a physician turned neuro‚Äëtechnology entrepreneur driven to improve mental health care. Previously, he was involved in clinical development, fundraising, and ultimately securing regulatory clearance and national insurance reimbursement for an AI-powered medical device at a Japanese med-tech startup. He then moved to the United States to found Universal¬†Brain in 2022, tackling a fundamental gap in psychiatry: the routine measurement of brain function.Universal¬†Brain‚Äôs platform captures well-validated brain function measures, called event-related potentials (ERPs), that reflect core neural processes linked to depression and its treatment. By turning these EEG‚Äëbased measures into a scalable, clinic‚Äëready tool, he aims to make objective brain‚Äëfunction testing a standard component of mental‚Äëhealth care to get better outcomes‚Äîstarting with depression and expanding across psychiatric conditions.

‚Äã4\. **[Allison M. Leopold Tilley](https://www.linkedin.com/in/allison-leopold-tilley/)** Partner at Pillsbury Winthrop Shaw Pittman LLP

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=1200/editor-images/1y/4b3fcbc0-9b45-473a-9679-8cbb4e496148.webp)

‚Äã‚Äã **Allison Leopold Tilley is named one of the top ‚ÄúWomen Leaders in Tech Law‚Äù by** **_The Recorder_** **for six consecutive years and hailed as the Technology ‚ÄúDealmaker of the Year‚Äù by** **_The Deal._** **Based in Silicon Valley, Allison advises technology companies, including on their formation, venture capital financings, multibillion-dollar M&As, public offerings, securities transactions, SPAC transactions and board governance.**

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãHosts: Davinci Cafe: Where thinkers, creators, and visionaries from every industry connect, collaborate, and shape the future. Find your tribe, your partners, and your inspiration.

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãSponsors: Pillsbury Winthrop Shaw Pittman LLP: ‚Äã‚ÄãA global law firm focusing on the Tech, Energy, Financial, Real Estate & Construction, and Life Sciences industries.

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã _Please note, this event may be photographed and filmed. Davinci Cafe reserves the right to use photographs and video from the event for marketing and communications purposes. By attending the event you consent to your image being used for these purposes._

column14: Khalid Altalib is a Sudanese-American filmmaker and artist known for his documentary work exploring themes of identity, migration, and displacement. He gained significant recognition for directing the critically acclaimed documentary "Khartoum Offside," which chronicles the challenges and aspirations of a group of young female footballers in Sudan. Altalib's films often offer intimate and nuanced perspectives on contemporary social and political issues within the Sudanese diaspora and beyond. He is committed to using his storytelling to amplify marginalized voices and foster cross-cultural understanding. His work has been showcased at numerous international film festivals, earning him several awards and nominations.

About Event

‚ÄãJoin us for **AgentCon 2025**, the San Francisco stop on the **[AI Agents World Tour](https://globalai.community/chapters/san-francisco/events/agentcon-2025-san-francisco/)** ‚Äî a global series of one-day conferences designed exclusively for developers building the future with AI agents.

‚ÄãExpect an evening of high-impact learning and collaboration with **5 featured speakers**, a workshop, and expert hub meetups, including experts from **Microsoft, Neon,** and the founders of leading AI agent startups. The event is FREE TO ATTEND.

Whether you're building intelligent assistants, autonomous tools, or real-time developer workflows, this event is your front-row seat to the future of AI agents.

‚Äã **What to Expect:**

- ‚Äãüîç Session Talks for a 15¬†+ 5 minutes Q&A from AI pioneers and industry leaders.

- ‚Äãüõ† Hands-On Workshop on how to build an agent, deploy, and scale in 30 minutes.

- ‚Äãüí¨ Expert Hub Meetup ‚Äî An informal space where attendees can ask follow-up questions and dive deeper with speakers and experts

- ‚Äã‚öôÔ∏è Live Demos of powerful open-source frameworks and tools with AI experts.

- ‚Äãü§ù Networking with a global community of builders, hackers, and innovators.


‚ÄãThis isn‚Äôt just another AI event ‚Äî it‚Äôs where developers meet to talk real code, share insights, and shape what‚Äôs next.

# ‚Äã **Talks & Speakers**

‚Äã **‚ÄãGabriela de Quieroz**, Director of AI - Microsoft for Startups, will moderate the event and lead the conversation with our speakers.

**CALL FOR SPEAKERS**

CFP is open for speakers till the 30th of May, we'd be thrilled to feature you as one of our¬†**headline speakers** for a 15¬†+ 5 minutes Q&A session. Apply with your speaking proposal using this link:

[https://sessionize.com/agentcon-2025-san-francisco/](https://sessionize.com/agentcon-2025-san-francisco/)

# ‚Äã **Sponsors**

‚Äã‚ÄãThis event is organized in partnership with Global AI Community, GitHub, and Neon.

## ‚ÄãAbout Global AI Community

‚ÄãThe Global AI Community is an international not-for-profit organisation with a focus on helping people learn about AI by connecting local communities around the world. Our mission is to promote, educate, and advance a diverse AI community through outreach, education, conferences, events and social gatherings. Learn more at [globalai.community](http://globalai.community/).

## ‚Äã‚ÄãAbout Neon

‚Äã‚ÄãNeon takes everything developers love about Postgres ‚Äî reliability, performance, extensibility ‚Äî and delivers it as a serverless product that helps you ship reliable, scalable applications faster than ever. Learn more about Neon at [neon.tech](http://neon.tech/).

About Event

‚ÄãJoin [Inception Studio](http://inceptionstudio.org/) and [Carta](https://carta.com/) for an exclusive deep dive into the latest AI fundraising trends in 2025.

Featuring [Peter Walker](https://www.linkedin.com/in/peterjameswalker/), Head of Insights at Carta, this intimate event is reserved for our community of founders, AI leaders, and network of top VCs at the leading edge of AI investments.

Evening Agenda

4:00 - 4:10: Introductions from Carta and inception Studio

‚Äã4:30 - 4:50: Fireside chat with Peter with co founder and Managing Partner at Inception Studio Capital, John Whaley, moderated by Tiffine Wang

About Carta

Through a connected ecosystem of tools, Carta links together the key players in private equity and venture ‚Äî from investors and LPs to their portfolio companies. Trusted by more than 40,000 companies, Carta helps private businesses manage their cap tables, valuations, taxes, equity programs, compensation, and more.

About Inception Studio Capital: A Silicon Valley fund investing in experienced founders building AI-native companies. We leverage our zero-equity founder community to attract serial entrepreneurs, domain experts, and technical leaders who are reshaping industries through AI-first approaches. 205 experienced founders, 38 companies launched, $142M+ raised.

column14: Respira is a certified breathwork and movement facilitator dedicated to helping individuals connect with their inner calm and physical awareness. With a focus on mindful movement and conscious breathing techniques, Respira guides participants toward improved well-being and stress reduction. They believe in the power of simple practices to unlock deeper self-understanding and enhance overall health. Their expertise lies in creating accessible and inclusive sessions that empower individuals to find their own unique rhythm and breath. Respira's approach is gentle, encouraging, and rooted in the belief that everyone can benefit from the transformative potential of breath and movement.

His work revolves around providing VCs with the infrastructure and analysis needed to succeed in a competitive market. He is actively involved in building and shaping the next generation of venture capital technology.

column1: Early Stage Summit

28

# ‚Äã **We're sold out! üéâ Check out the resources below to learn more about us and stay updated on future events!**

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **JOIN OUR EMAIL LIST -** [https://forms.gle/eESV3EAJicPfC2oP6](https://forms.gle/eESV3EAJicPfC2oP6)

‚Äãüåç **What if the key to fighting climate change starts with stopping cows from burping methane?**

‚ÄãJoin us at The Wave as we host **Alex Brown**, cofounder and CEO of **Alga Biosciences**, a startup tackling a major contributor to climate change: methane emissions from cows. By preventing this potent greenhouse gas at the source, Alga is rethinking what climate solutions can look like.

‚ÄãIn this talk, we‚Äôll explore the bigger picture:

‚Äì What‚Äôs the right _order of operations_ for tackling the climate crisis?

‚Äì Can we _depoliticize_ climate change?

‚Äì What role should _capitalism_ play in solving it?

‚Äì And how do we balance _evolution_ vs. _revolution_ in industry?

‚ÄãThe answers may not be clear-cut, but this conversation will spark new ideas, challenge old assumptions, and leave us all with a little more hope about the future. üå±

# ‚Äã‚ùìFAQs‚ùì

## ‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãWhat should I expect?

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã7:00-7:40 --> arrival & chats

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã7:40-8:20 --> lecture

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã8:20-9:00 --> q&a and more chatting

## ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **Who's invited?**

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãAnyone with an interest in learning new things, meeting new people, and doing fun things on weeknights! Lots of people came solo to our last event, so don't be afraid to do the same‚Äîyou‚Äôll meet some awesome people!

## ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **What about parking?**

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãThere's no parking on-site, so we recommend street parking or using public transportation.

## ‚Äã **Do I have to be 21+?**

‚ÄãNo :) This venue is open to all ages.

## ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **What about refunds?**

‚ÄãYou can refund your ticket up to 24 hours before the event starts. Since this is a limited-space event, we encourage you to update your RSVP if you can‚Äôt make it‚Äîthis helps us keep spots open for others.

## ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **I can't make it to this event. How do I stay updated for future events?**

‚Äã‚ÄãJoin our email list! [https://forms.gle/GQdDjd2UTV48F5Z17](https://forms.gle/GQdDjd2UTV48F5Z17)

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãFollow our Instagram! [https://www.instagram.com/bigbrainsf/](https://www.instagram.com/bigbrainsf/)

## ‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãHow do I become a speaker?

‚Äã‚Äã‚ÄãEmail _bigbrainsanfrancisco@gmail.com_ with your name, a brief description of who you are, and what you're passionate about / researching.

## ‚Äã‚ÄãAbout Our Ticket Structure

‚ÄãWe‚Äôre not taking a profit‚Äîevery ticket sold goes directly back into the business. Our pricing also depends on the venue, and this space charges us a rental fee, which is why tickets for this event are slightly higher than previous ones.

‚ÄãThat said, we‚Äôre committed to making our events accessible to everyone. If cost is a barrier, please don‚Äôt hesitate to reach out by emailing us at **bigbrainsanfrancisco@gmail.com**‚Äîwe reserve a handful of tickets for financial assistance at every event.

‚ÄãThanks for supporting our growing mission!

‚Äã‚Äã **_\*For any other questions or special accommodations, please email bigbrainsanfrancisco@gmail.com._**

column14: Alex Brown is the Co-founder and CEO of Alga Biosciences, a company focused on developing sustainable and nutritional ingredients from algae. His background lies in biological sciences and biotechnology, with a focus on leveraging algal biomass for various applications. Brown's leadership at Alga Biosciences centers around creating scalable and cost-effective methods for algae cultivation and processing. He aims to transform the food, feed, and materials industries with algae-derived products. Under his guidance, Alga Biosciences seeks to address environmental challenges while delivering valuable products.

column14: Anna Binder is the Chief People Officer at Asana, a work management platform. She leads the company's people strategy, overseeing talent acquisition, employee experience, diversity and inclusion, and compensation & benefits. Binder is passionate about fostering a culture where employees can thrive and do their best work. She has been with Asana since 2013, contributing significantly to its growth and recognition as a top workplace. Her focus is on building a values-driven organization that prioritizes employee well-being and development.

## ‚Äã **What is this?‚Äã**

‚ÄãIt‚Äôs an intimate founders gathering designed for meaningful, in-depth conversations.

‚ÄãBuilding a startup in San Francisco isn‚Äôt just about the idea‚Äîit‚Äôs about the people around you. That‚Äôs why we‚Äôre creating a space where tech founders can connect, share insights, and find real opportunities‚Äîwhether it‚Äôs a co-founder, investor, client, or simply a like-minded friend.

‚ÄãThis isn‚Äôt a typical networking event. It‚Äôs an intimate gathering designed for meaningful, in-depth conversations. You‚Äôll have the time and space to dive into:

- ‚ÄãWhere your startup stands today and where it‚Äôs headed

- ‚ÄãThe biggest challenges you‚Äôre facing right now

- ‚ÄãYour long-term vision and how to get there


‚ÄãExpect fresh perspectives, actionable advice, and a community that genuinely supports your success. If you're looking for more than just business cards‚Äîif you‚Äôre seeking real conversations that move the needle‚Äîthis is the place to be.

‚Äã‚Äã **"TÔªøhis event is ONLY for founders/CEO & C Levels"**

‚Äã‚ÄãOur event boasts an impressive lineup of attendees, including esteemed individuals from renowned organizations such as Y Combinator, 500 Startups, and numerous talented founders from across the globe.

‚Äã‚ÄãThe majority of these attendees are **exceptional pre-seed to series A founders** who have demonstrated significant traction in their respective fields. We are delighted to bring together such a diverse and accomplished group of individuals, creating an invaluable networking and learning opportunity for all participants.

column14: Kyosuke Togami is the head of the Togami family, a powerful and influential group, and brother to Byakuya Togami, though they are not related by blood. Kyosuke is known for his calculating and ruthless nature, prioritizing the family's business interests above all else. He played a significant role in the Future Foundation and took responsibility for overseeing the rehabilitation of the Remnants of Despair. While possessing similar intelligence and strategic thinking as his brother, Kyosuke's methods are often more pragmatic and less reliant on personal pride. His ultimate goal is to maintain the Togami family's dominance and contribute to rebuilding society after the Tragedy.

## ‚Äã **‚Äãüë´This Founders Gatherings will be led by MindPal & Tuttii**

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=202.734375/editor-images/j3/74f48a9c-8922-4eb3-86b4-ddbc3e0d9482.png)

‚Äã [MindPal.co](http://mindpal.co/)¬†is an innovative technology partner dedicated to empowering startups and fast-growing tech companies in the AI era. We specialize in building intelligent, automated solutions that help founders accelerate business growth, attract investors, and scale globally.

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=418.6666666666667/editor-images/xo/d5783798-d37d-4498-b4bb-edf1bd76c0cf.png)

Our first-of-their-kind platform partnerships and music licensing structures eliminate copyright concerns for end users sharing to social media, while also ensuring proper attribution for artists and songwriters.

* * *

## ‚Äã **What is this?‚Äã**

‚ÄãIt‚Äôs an intimate founders gathering designed for meaningful, in-depth conversations.

‚ÄãBuilding a startup in San Francisco isn‚Äôt just about the idea‚Äîit‚Äôs about the people around you. That‚Äôs why we‚Äôre creating a space where tech founders can connect, share insights, and find real opportunities‚Äîwhether it‚Äôs a co-founder, investor, client, or simply a like-minded friend.

‚ÄãThis isn‚Äôt a typical networking event. It‚Äôs an intimate gathering designed for meaningful, in-depth conversations. You‚Äôll have the time and space to dive into:

- ‚ÄãWhere your startup stands today and where it‚Äôs headed

- ‚ÄãThe biggest challenges you‚Äôre facing right now

- ‚ÄãYour long-term vision and how to get there


‚ÄãExpect fresh perspectives, actionable advice, and a community that genuinely supports your success. If you're looking for more than just business cards‚Äîif you‚Äôre seeking real conversations that move the needle‚Äîthis is the place to be.

‚Äã‚Äã **"TÔªøhis event is ONLY for founders/CEO & C Levels"**

‚Äã‚ÄãOur event boasts an impressive lineup of attendees, including esteemed individuals from renowned organizations such as Y Combinator, 500 Startups, and numerous talented founders from across the globe.

‚Äã‚ÄãThe majority of these attendees are **exceptional pre-seed to series A founders** who have demonstrated significant traction in their respective fields. We are delighted to bring together such a diverse and accomplished group of individuals, creating an invaluable networking and learning opportunity for all participants.

* * *

‚Äã‚Äã **\*ÔªøPlease note that if you register but are unable to attend without notifying us in advance, we may not be able to extend future invitations to you. Your cooperation in this matter is greatly appreciated.**

column14: Lucas Sojka is a Polish filmmaker and visual artist known for his distinctive style that blends documentary realism with poetic and symbolic elements. He often explores themes of memory, identity, and the human condition in his films, using experimental techniques and striking imagery. Sojka gained recognition for his short films and has since moved into feature-length projects. He is particularly interested in exploring complex social and political issues through deeply personal and often visually arresting narratives. Sojka's work has been showcased at numerous international film festivals, earning him critical acclaim and awards.

## ‚Äã **What is this?‚Äã**

‚ÄãIt‚Äôs an intimate founders gathering designed for meaningful, in-depth conversations.

‚ÄãBuilding a startup in San Francisco isn‚Äôt just about the idea‚Äîit‚Äôs about the people around you. That‚Äôs why we‚Äôre creating a space where tech founders can connect, share insights, and find real opportunities‚Äîwhether it‚Äôs a co-founder, investor, client, or simply a like-minded friend.

‚ÄãThis isn‚Äôt a typical networking event. It‚Äôs an intimate gathering designed for meaningful, in-depth conversations. You‚Äôll have the time and space to dive into:

- ‚ÄãWhere your startup stands today and where it‚Äôs headed

- ‚ÄãThe biggest challenges you‚Äôre facing right now

- ‚ÄãYour long-term vision and how to get there


‚ÄãExpect fresh perspectives, actionable advice, and a community that genuinely supports your success. If you're looking for more than just business cards‚Äîif you‚Äôre seeking real conversations that move the needle‚Äîthis is the place to be.

‚Äã‚Äã **"TÔªøhis event is ONLY for founders/CEO & C Levels"**

‚Äã‚ÄãOur event boasts an impressive lineup of attendees, including esteemed individuals from renowned organizations such as Y Combinator, 500 Startups, and numerous talented founders from across the globe.

‚Äã‚ÄãThe majority of these attendees are **exceptional pre-seed to series A founders** who have demonstrated significant traction in their respective fields. We are delighted to bring together such a diverse and accomplished group of individuals, creating an invaluable networking and learning opportunity for all participants.

* * *

‚Äã‚Äã **\*ÔªøPlease note that if you register but are unable to attend without notifying us in advance, we may not be able to extend future invitations to you. Your cooperation in this matter is greatly appreciated.**

column14: Troy Skinner is a software engineer and cybersecurity expert known for his contributions to secure coding practices. He has worked in various roles focused on penetration testing, vulnerability analysis, and security architecture. Skinner is actively involved in educating developers about writing more secure code and mitigating common security risks. He frequently speaks at conferences and workshops on topics related to application security and threat modeling. His expertise helps organizations improve their overall cybersecurity posture.

Prior to Take2, Joyce gained experience in various roles within the media and communications landscape. She has a passion for storytelling and empowering individuals through shared knowledge.

column14: Gloria Liu is a host at Take2, a channel on YouTube that focuses on providing comprehensive explanations of popular TV shows and movies. She is known for her clear and engaging communication style, making complex plot points and character arcs easily digestible for viewers. Liu's background includes experience in media production and content creation. She has a talent for summarizing intricate storylines and identifying key themes, helping audiences deepen their understanding and appreciation of the shows they watch. Her expertise contributes to Take2's success in delivering high-quality entertainment analysis.

**Emmett Shear** served as CEO of Twitch until recently when he started his new company, [Softmax](https://softmax.com/), with the mission to solve the AI alignment problem.

In this in person Ask Me Anything session, we will discuss with Emmett the mission of Softmax, how he envisions tackling the AI alignment problem, AGI, post-AGI scenarios, building an AI company in 2025, and many other topics.

column14: Emmett Shear is a co-founder of Twitch, the popular live video streaming platform, and served as its CEO for over 15 years. He previously co-founded Justin.tv, the precursor to Twitch, with Justin Kan, Michael Seibel, and Kyle Vogt. Under Shear's leadership, Twitch was acquired by Amazon in 2014 for nearly $1 billion. In March 2023, he stepped down as Twitch CEO. He is currently the CEO of Softmax, an AI company focused on creating beneficial intelligence through "cooperative AI."

column11: Peter Walker is the Head of Insights at Carta, focusing on cutting through private market noise with data-driven signal. Prior to Carta, he was the Head of Marketing at the media analytics company, PublicRelay. He also helped create the data visualization team for The Atlantic magazine's Covid Tracking Project. Milly Wang is a Vice President at 65 Equity Partners, a global investment firm that is backed by Temasek and has US$3.3 billion in funds under management. She previously worked in Private Equity at Carrick Capital Partners, and as an Investment Banking Analyst at J.P. Morgan prior to that. Milly holds a B.A. in Economics and Statistics from Harvard College and an MBA from Harvard Business School. Tom Nakata is the Co-founder and CEO of Qlay. He previously worked as a consultant at McKinsey, building organizational and marketing strategies for Consumer Packaged Goods (CPG) brands. Tom received his B.A. in Statistics from Harvard College.

* * *

‚ÄãJoin us for an exciting gathering in San Francisco that connects enterprise leaders with leading startup founders! Hear insights on latest trends in AI startups and VC funding from industry experts.

‚ÄãThis event is hosted by **[Qlay](https://qlay.ai/lp/su/v1)** **,** **[Digital Garage US](https://dg717.com/)** and **[Open Network Lab](https://onlab.jp/)**.

## ‚Äã **Guest Speakers**

‚Äã **[Peter Walker](https://www.linkedin.com/in/peterjameswalker/overlay/about-this-profile/)** is the Head of Insights at **[Carta](https://carta.com/)**, focusing on cutting through private market noise with data-driven signal. Prior to Carta, he was the Head of Marketing at the media analytics company, [PublicRelay](https://publicrelay.com/). He also helped create the data visualization team for The Atlantic magazine's Covid Tracking Project.

‚Äã **[Milly Wang](https://www.linkedin.com/in/wangmilly/overlay/about-this-profile/)** is a Vice President at **[65 Equity Partners](https://www.65equitypartners.com/)**, a global investment firm that is backed by [Temasek](https://www.temasek.com.sg/) and has US$3.3 billion in funds under management. She previously worked in Private Equity at [Carrick Capital Partners](https://www.carrickcapitalpartners.com/), and as an Investment Banking Analyst at [J.P. Morgan](https://www.jpmorgan.com/) prior to that. Milly holds a B.A. in Economics and Statistics from [Harvard College](https://college.harvard.edu/) and an MBA from [Harvard Business School](https://www.hbs.edu/).

## ‚Äã **Moderator**

‚Äã **[Tom Nakata](https://www.linkedin.com/in/tnakata/overlay/about-this-profile/)** is the Co-founder and CEO of **[Qlay](https://qlay.ai/lp/su/v1)**. He previously worked as a consultant at [McKinsey](https://www.mckinsey.com/), building organizational and marketing strategies for Consumer Packaged Goods (CPG) brands. Tom received his B.A. in Statistics from [Harvard College](https://college.harvard.edu/).

- ‚Äã6:45 - 7:10 pm: Fireside chat with **[Milly Wang](https://www.linkedin.com/in/wangmilly/overlay/about-this-profile/)** (Vice President at **[65 Equity Partners](https://www.65equitypartners.com/)**), moderated by **[Tom Nakata](https://www.linkedin.com/in/tnakata/)** (Co-founder and CEO of **[Qlay](https://qlay.ai/lp/su/v1)**)

- ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã7:10 - 7:15 pm: Announcements

# ‚Äã **‚Äã‚ÄãHosts**

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **[Qlay](https://qlay.ai/lp/su/v1)** is a Global Engineer Hiring Platform. We help startups source, screen and hire top-tier engineers from around the world. [Book a quick intro call](https://qlay.ai/request-demo) to learn how you can scale your development without ruining your cash flow!

‚Äã **[Open Network Lab](https://onlab.jp/)**(OnLab) is a seed accelerator program run by the [Digital Garage Group](https://www.garage.co.jp/). There are 2 batches a year with an investment of $100K.

‚Äã **[Digital Garage US](https://dg717.com/)** is a technology incubator that bridges global markets and industries. By leveraging its diverse international network, Digital Garage US empowers startups, creators, and businesses to expand and innovate on a worldwide stage.

column14: Peter Walker is the Head of Insights at Carta, where he leads a team that analyzes private market data to provide valuable insights for stakeholders. His work focuses on leveraging Carta's extensive dataset on equity ownership and compensation to understand trends in startups and private companies. He frequently presents data-driven analyses on topics like startup compensation, employee equity, and the broader venture capital landscape. His aim is to make private markets more transparent and accessible through data and research.

column1: Founder Ownership in AI Startups and VC Funding Trends
column2: Join us for an exciting gathering in San Francisco that connects enterprise leaders with leading startup founders! Hear insights on latest trends in AI startups and VC funding from industry experts.
column11: Peter Walker is the Head of Insights at Carta, focusing on cutting through private market noise with data-driven signal. Prior to Carta, he was the Head of Marketing at the media analytics company, PublicRelay. He also helped create the data visualization team for The Atlantic magazine's Covid Tracking Project. Milly Wang is a Vice President at 65 Equity Partners, a global investment firm that is backed by Temasek and has US$3.3 billion in funds under management. She previously worked in Private Equity at Carrick Capital Partners, and as an Investment Banking Analyst at J.P. Morgan prior to that. Milly holds a B.A. in Economics and Statistics from Harvard College and an MBA from Harvard Business School. Tom Nakata is the Co-founder and CEO of Qlay. He previously worked as a consultant at McKinsey, building organizational and marketing strategies for Consumer Packaged Goods (CPG) brands. Tom received his B.A. in Statistics from Harvard College.

About Event

‚Äã **_Note:_** _This is a hybrid event. For online participation, please register from this URL instead:_

‚Äã [https://www.linkedin.com/events/founderownershipinaistartupsand7330346074282385409/](https://www.linkedin.com/events/founderownershipinaistartupsand7330346074282385409/)

* * *

‚ÄãJoin us for an exciting gathering in San Francisco that connects enterprise leaders with leading startup founders! Hear insights on latest trends in AI startups and VC funding from industry experts.

‚ÄãThis event is hosted by **[Qlay](https://qlay.ai/lp/su/v1)** **,** **[Digital Garage US](https://dg717.com/)** and **[Open Network Lab](https://onlab.jp/)**.

## ‚Äã **Guest Speakers**

‚Äã **[Peter Walker](https://www.linkedin.com/in/peterjameswalker/overlay/about-this-profile/)** is the Head of Insights at **[Carta](https://carta.com/)**, focusing on cutting through private market noise with data-driven signal. Prior to Carta, he was the Head of Marketing at the media analytics company, [PublicRelay](https://publicrelay.com/). He also helped create the data visualization team for The Atlantic magazine's Covid Tracking Project.

‚Äã **[Milly Wang](https://www.linkedin.com/in/wangmilly/overlay/about-this-profile/)** is a Vice President at **[65 Equity Partners](https://www.65equitypartners.com/)**, a global investment firm that is backed by [Temasek](https://www.temasek.com.sg/) and has US$3.3 billion in funds under management. She previously worked in Private Equity at [Carrick Capital Partners](https://www.carrickcapitalpartners.com/), and as an Investment Banking Analyst at [J.P. Morgan](https://www.jpmorgan.com/) prior to that. Milly holds a B.A. in Economics and Statistics from [Harvard College](https://college.harvard.edu/) and an MBA from [Harvard Business School](https://www.hbs.edu/).

## ‚Äã **Moderator**

‚Äã **[Tom Nakata](https://www.linkedin.com/in/tnakata/overlay/about-this-profile/)** is the Co-founder and CEO of **[Qlay](https://qlay.ai/lp/su/v1)**. He previously worked as a consultant at [McKinsey](https://www.mckinsey.com/), building organizational and marketing strategies for Consumer Packaged Goods (CPG) brands. Tom received his B.A. in Statistics from [Harvard College](https://college.harvard.edu/).

# ‚Äã **Agenda**

- ‚Äã5‚Äã‚Äã:30 - 6:15 pm: Registration and Networking w/ Food and Drinks!‚Äã

- ‚Äã6:15 - 6:20 pm: Partner Introductions‚Äã

- ‚Äã6:20 - 6:45 pm: Presentation by **[Peter Walker](https://www.linkedin.com/in/peterjameswalker/overlay/about-this-profile/)** (Head of Insights at **[Carta](https://carta.com/)**)

- ‚Äã6:45 - 7:10 pm: Fireside chat with **[Milly Wang](https://www.linkedin.com/in/wangmilly/overlay/about-this-profile/)** (Vice President at **[65 Equity Partners](https://www.65equitypartners.com/)**), moderated by **[Tom Nakata](https://www.linkedin.com/in/tnakata/)** (Co-founder and CEO of **[Qlay](https://qlay.ai/lp/su/v1)**)

- ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã7:10 - 7:15 pm: Announcements

- ‚Äã7:15 - 8:00 pm: Networking


# ‚Äã **‚Äã‚ÄãHosts**

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **[Qlay](https://qlay.ai/lp/su/v1)** is a Global Engineer Hiring Platform. We help startups source, screen and hire top-tier engineers from around the world. [Book a quick intro call](https://qlay.ai/request-demo) to learn how you can scale your development without ruining your cash flow!

‚Äã **[Open Network Lab](https://onlab.jp/)**(OnLab) is a seed accelerator program run by the [Digital Garage Group](https://www.garage.co.jp/). There are 2 batches a year with an investment of $100K.

‚Äã **[Digital Garage US](https://dg717.com/)** is a technology incubator that bridges global markets and industries. By leveraging its diverse international network, Digital Garage US empowers startups, creators, and businesses to expand and innovate on a worldwide stage.

column14: Milly Wang is a Vice President at 65 Equity Partners, a Singapore-based investment firm. She focuses on growth equity investments across Southeast Asia. Prior to joining 65 Equity Partners, she gained experience in investment banking and private equity, working with companies across various sectors. Her responsibilities include deal sourcing, due diligence, deal execution, and portfolio management. She brings a strong analytical background and a passion for supporting growing businesses in the region.

column1: Founder Ownership in AI Startups and VC Funding Trends
column2: Join us for an exciting gathering in San Francisco that connects enterprise leaders with leading startup founders! Hear insights on latest trends in AI startups and VC funding from industry experts.
column11: Peter Walker is the Head of Insights at Carta, focusing on cutting through private market noise with data-driven signal. Prior to Carta, he was the Head of Marketing at the media analytics company, PublicRelay. He also helped create the data visualization team for The Atlantic magazine's Covid Tracking Project. Milly Wang is a Vice President at 65 Equity Partners, a global investment firm that is backed by Temasek and has US$3.3 billion in funds under management. She previously worked in Private Equity at Carrick Capital Partners, and as an Investment Banking Analyst at J.P. Morgan prior to that. Milly holds a B.A. in Economics and Statistics from Harvard College and an MBA from Harvard Business School. Tom Nakata is the Co-founder and CEO of Qlay. He previously worked as a consultant at McKinsey, building organizational and marketing strategies for Consumer Packaged Goods (CPG) brands. Tom received his B.A. in Statistics from Harvard College.

‚ÄãJoin us for an exciting gathering in San Francisco that connects enterprise leaders with leading startup founders! Hear insights on latest trends in AI startups and VC funding from industry experts.

‚ÄãThis event is hosted by **[Qlay](https://qlay.ai/lp/su/v1)** **,** **[Digital Garage US](https://dg717.com/)** and **[Open Network Lab](https://onlab.jp/)**.

## ‚Äã **Guest Speakers**

‚Äã **[Peter Walker](https://www.linkedin.com/in/peterjameswalker/overlay/about-this-profile/)** is the Head of Insights at **[Carta](https://carta.com/)**, focusing on cutting through private market noise with data-driven signal. Prior to Carta, he was the Head of Marketing at the media analytics company, [PublicRelay](https://publicrelay.com/). He also helped create the data visualization team for The Atlantic magazine's Covid Tracking Project.

‚Äã **[Milly Wang](https://www.linkedin.com/in/wangmilly/overlay/about-this-profile/)** is a Vice President at **[65 Equity Partners](https://www.65equitypartners.com/)**, a global investment firm that is backed by [Temasek](https://www.temasek.com.sg/) and has US$3.3 billion in funds under management. She previously worked in Private Equity at [Carrick Capital Partners](https://www.carrickcapitalpartners.com/), and as an Investment Banking Analyst at [J.P. Morgan](https://www.jpmorgan.com/) prior to that. Milly holds a B.A. in Economics and Statistics from [Harvard College](https://college.harvard.edu/) and an MBA from [Harvard Business School](https://www.hbs.edu/).

## ‚Äã **Moderator**

‚Äã **[Tom Nakata](https://www.linkedin.com/in/tnakata/overlay/about-this-profile/)** is the Co-founder and CEO of **[Qlay](https://qlay.ai/lp/su/v1)**. He previously worked as a consultant at [McKinsey](https://www.mckinsey.com/), building organizational and marketing strategies for Consumer Packaged Goods (CPG) brands. Tom received his B.A. in Statistics from [Harvard College](https://college.harvard.edu/).

- ‚Äã5‚Äã‚Äã:30 - 6:15 pm: Registration and Networking w/ Food and Drinks!‚Äã

- ‚Äã6:45 - 7:10 pm: Fireside chat with **[Milly Wang](https://www.linkedin.com/in/wangmilly/overlay/about-this-profile/)** (Vice President at **[65 Equity Partners](https://www.65equitypartners.com/)**), moderated by **[Tom Nakata](https://www.linkedin.com/in/tnakata/)** (Co-founder and CEO of **[Qlay](https://qlay.ai/lp/su/v1)**)

# ‚Äã **‚Äã‚ÄãHosts**

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **[Qlay](https://qlay.ai/lp/su/v1)** is a Global Engineer Hiring Platform. We help startups source, screen and hire top-tier engineers from around the world. [Book a quick intro call](https://qlay.ai/request-demo) to learn how you can scale your development without ruining your cash flow!

‚Äã **[Open Network Lab](https://onlab.jp/)**(OnLab) is a seed accelerator program run by the [Digital Garage Group](https://www.garage.co.jp/). There are 2 batches a year with an investment of $100K.

‚Äã **[Digital Garage US](https://dg717.com/)** is a technology incubator that bridges global markets and industries. By leveraging its diverse international network, Digital Garage US empowers startups, creators, and businesses to expand and innovate on a worldwide stage.

column14: Tom Nakata is the Co-founder and CEO of Qlay, a company focused on leveraging AI and generative AI to transform data workflows. He possesses a background in product management and has experience in building and scaling AI-powered solutions. Prior to Qlay, Nakata held leadership positions at companies like Facebook (Meta) and Figure Eight (now Appen). His expertise lies in bridging the gap between cutting-edge AI technology and practical business applications. Nakata is passionate about democratizing access to AI for enterprises.

# üìö Short Story Symposium \[public\]

Hosted by Mendel Liu & The SF Commons

May

28

Wednesday, May 28

6:30 PM - 7:30 PM PDT

[550 Laguna St\\
\\
San Francisco, California](https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=550%20Laguna%20St&query_place_id=ChIJQ9xlT6KAhYAReQIfVQZP4ds)

Welcome! To join the event, please register below.

Register

You will be asked to verify token ownership with your wallet.

About Event

‚ÄãNote: while there are many guests listed in the RSVP, most of these are carried over from previous events in this series. We don't expect much more than 30 to attend.

I'm interested in having some laid-back yet stimulating conversations about some of my favorite pieces of short fiction.

‚ÄãA general aim of the stories will be to explore alternative possible worlds through fiction with the hope of gaining more insight into our own. To that end, many of the short stories will include an element of futurism, speculation, and social commentary. We‚Äôll feature authors like Ted Chiang, Ursula K Le Guin, Greg Egan, and others.

Readings for 2025:

- ‚ÄãJanuary 22: _The Manamouki_, by Mike Resnick ( [Read](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1IrDpZy_44FNsmpIFy6CFiBxDKOZFYDG7/view?usp=drive_link))

  - ‚ÄãSequel to _Kirinyaga_, recommended but not required( [Read](https://www.baen.com/Chapters/034541702X/034541702X___1.htm))
- ‚ÄãFebruary 5: _Story of Your Life_, by Ted Chiang [(Read](https://raley.english.ucsb.edu/wp-content/uploads/Reading/Chiang-story.pdf) / [Listen](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q7K74v56MU8&t=12344s))

- ‚ÄãFebruary 19: _Houston, Houston, Do You Read_, by James Tiptree Jr ( [Read](https://www.sfsfss.com/stories/HoustonHouston.html))

- ‚ÄãMarch 12: _The People of Sand and Slag_, by Paolo Bacigalupi ( [Read](https://windupstories.com/books/pump-six-and-other-stories/people-of-sand-and-slag/))

- ‚ÄãApril 2: _A Word for Heathens_, by Peter Watts ( [Read](https://rifters.com/real/shorts/PeterWatts_Heathens.pdf))

- ‚ÄãApril 23: _A Little Knowledge_, by Mike Resnick ( [Read](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1rMIfMicmiI04aFAzOK9kNsFLI4Mq-sc7/view?usp=drive_link))

  - ‚ÄãSequel to _The Manamouki_, recommended but not required ( [Read](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1IrDpZy_44FNsmpIFy6CFiBxDKOZFYDG7/view?usp=drive_link))
- ‚ÄãMay 28: _Black Mirror - San Junipero_ ( [Watch](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1M7IogtugYBix4FUUVsnkW0mJCIi-mZq5/view?usp=drive_link))


‚ÄãReadings for 2024:

- ‚ÄãJanuary 24: _The Ones Who Walk Away From Omelas_, by Ursula K Le Guin ( [Read](https://shsdavisapes.pbworks.com/f/Omelas.pdf))

- ‚ÄãFebruary 7: _Liking What You See: A Documentary_, by Ted Chiang ( [Read](https://www.are.na/block/8515263) / [Listen](https://youtu.be/Q7K74v56MU8?t=31731))

- ‚ÄãFebruary 21: _Learning to be Me_, by Greg Egan ( [Read](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1xbpHrbm4e2vbaj4WTwGPea_G1NXgKiD8/view?usp=share_link))

- ‚ÄãMarch 6: _Exhalation_, by Ted Chiang ( [Read](https://www.lightspeedmagazine.com/fiction/exhalation/) / [Listen](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mNbfU2gAnXE))

- ‚ÄãMarch 20: _Nine Lives_, by Ursula K Le Guin ( [Read](http://www.baen.com/Chapters/9781625791405/9781625791405___2.htm))

- ‚ÄãApril 3: _The Merchant and The Alchemist's Gate_, by Ted Chiang ( [Read](https://www.are.na/block/4550302) / [Listen](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VYXqBW4ink))

- ‚ÄãApril 17: _Bloodchild_, by Octavia Butler ( [Read](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1IPRE6zIE7btsUzjwWsN4DL2h15XeMfiZ/view?usp=share_link))

- ‚ÄãMay 15: _Omphalos_, by Ted Chiang ( [Read](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1_F438WQLHuDvCASaIfe4k_WpAa9HdBx8/view?usp=share_link))

- ‚ÄãJune 5: _Chrysalis_, by Mary Robinette Kowal ( [Read](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1fbOJ-H9ffy0UjvNAZWwyJu_3ne8JQE2q/view?usp=share_link))

- ‚ÄãJune 19: _Kirinyaga_, by Mike Resnick ( [Read](https://www.baen.com/Chapters/034541702X/034541702X___1.htm))

- ‚ÄãJuly 17: _Anxiety is the Dizziness of Freedom_, by Ted Chiang ( [Read](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1SMRRl6O83DLc_blvW6qUt0gZk4lBVwJD/view))

- ‚ÄãJuly 31: _Reasons to be Cheerful_, by Greg Egan ( [Read](https://www.utilitarianism.com/greg-egan/Reasons-To-Be-Cheerful.pdf))

- ‚ÄãAugust 14: _Tower of Babylon_, by Ted Chiang ( [Read](https://jenniecreatesclasses.files.wordpress.com/2021/03/tower_of_babylon_-_ted_chiang.pdf) / [Listen](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q7K74v56MU8))

- ‚ÄãAugust 28: _Kingsmeat_, by Orson Scott Card ( [Read](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1mgg1Zjw6Kht7bArKZCtvx6_m86qOR4lB/view?usp=drive_link))

- ‚ÄãSeptember 11: _Zima Blue_, by Alastair Reynolds ( [Read](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1QQNNWHw6DB5-bKgZJFxezcW3b0TSPxO9/view?usp=drive_link) / [Watch](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1QMrL4v0hzuQIK6AVaA6UxsgZLN3nLD_j/view?usp=drive_link))

- ‚ÄãSeptember 25: _The Truth of Fact, the Truth of Feeling_, by Ted Chiang ( [Read](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ZQoHLknbj8kcTdcMEvFnazu73YIBKO_g/view))

- ‚ÄãOctober 9: _Psycho Pass,_( [Watch Ep. 1](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ML-iqXrCS0A), [Watch Ep. 2](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nl4yNrI-Y8Q))

- ‚ÄãOctober 23: _For I have Touched the Sky_, by Mike Resnick ( [Read](https://www.baen.com/Chapters/034541702X/034541702X___2.htm))

  - ‚ÄãSequel to _Kirinyaga_, recommended but not required( [Read](https://www.baen.com/Chapters/034541702X/034541702X___1.htm))
- ‚ÄãNovember 6: _Flowers for Algernon_, by Daniel Keyes ( [Read](https://www.sdfo.org/gj/stories/flowersforalgernon.pdf) / [Listen](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FDfE0NaAfgg&list=PLeZZJJMLW02Vs_u9VWxwDt2SxcPwXmU_F&index=1))

- ‚ÄãNovember 20: _The Consciousness Problem_, by Mary Robinette Kowal ( [Read](https://www.lightspeedmagazine.com/fiction/the-consciousness-problem/))

- ‚ÄãDecember 11: _Hell is the Absence of God_, by Ted Chiang ( [Read](https://www.are.na/block/2764145) / [Listen](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q7K74v56MU8&t=27357s))


‚ÄãWe'll post links to each story well in advance of each meeting. You're strongly encouraged to read the stories ahead of time and bring any thoughts you'd like to discuss! Contact me by text if you're having trouble finding the location.

If you enjoy this event, you might also be interested in having similar discussions here: [https://lu.ma/thoughtexperiments](https://lu.ma/thoughtexperiments)

550 Laguna St

San Francisco, CA 94102, USA

About Event

‚Äã **Hey Founders, Investors & Tech Professionals! üå≠üèê**

‚Äã **Let's welcome the summer with a Fresh-Off-the-Grill BBQ party at the beautiful Golden Gate Park! üèû**

* * *

‚Äã **What‚Äôs Included?**

‚úÖ BBQ off the grill ‚Äì Classic American-style burgers & hotdogs (including vegan options)

‚úÖ Fresh juice and snacks

‚úÖ Volleyball setup ‚Äì mostly friendly and casual games (come in even if you haven't tried before)

‚úÖ A few cup games to spark some friendly competition

‚úÖ Chill music and a lot of laid back conversations

**Other Details:**

üç∫ BYOB ‚Äì Beer & Wine only (no glass bottles or liquor per park rules)

üç± Feel free to bring a favorite snack or dish to share (optional)

üöª Restrooms are available near Hellman Hollow

üë• Capped at 20 people to keep things intimate and friendly

‚ÄãWe‚Äôve already booked Table 6 at Marx Event Meadow with the park authority, so bring yourself and maybe a little bit of sunscreen, excited to see you all!‚òÄÔ∏è

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=533.3333333333334/editor-images/v7/497c9991-8197-4b5a-b480-4e0688160e42.jpg)

column14: Tysir Osman is the Founder of Spon Social, a platform focused on connecting creators with sponsorship opportunities. He recognized the challenges creators face in securing brand deals and built Spon Social to streamline the process. Osman's background blends technical expertise with a passion for empowering creators. He aims to democratize access to sponsorships, enabling creators of all sizes to monetize their content. His vision centers on fostering authentic partnerships between brands and the creator community.

# ‚ÄãAWS MCP Agents Hackathon

‚ÄãJoin us to build **cutting-edge AI agents** that push the limits of **LLMs and AI applications**!

# ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **üéâ** üèÜ **$50k+ in Prizes!**

## ‚ÄãüöÄ The Challenge

‚ÄãUnleash your creativity to craft an extraordinary **multimodal AI agent!** Your mission is to design and develop an intelligent agent that's capable of sophisticated reasoning, strategic decision-making, and interacting with various tools. Build something that solves real problems and demonstrates innovative approaches to AI.

‚Äãüé§¬†**Showcase Your Vision:**

You will have¬†**3 minutes**¬†to captivate the audience and judges with your innovative solution. Pitch your AI agent‚Äôs purpose, capabilities, and transformative impact to win prizes.

## ‚Äã‚ÄãThe Opportunity

‚Äã‚Äã **Win big at this hackathon!** Compete for a chance to grab prizes and present your best product.

‚Äã‚Äã **Maximize your creation with sponsor APIs:** Many sponsors offer powerful APIs that can enhance your projects. Explore and utilize sponsor products to win special prizes.

‚Äã‚Äã **Join a vibrant community:** Connect with fellow AI engineers, learn from industry experts, and gain valuable exposure for your work.

‚Äã **Meet investors:** Network with investors who are interested in enterprise AI innovations. Gain feedback, connections, and potential funding.

‚Äã‚Äã **Don't miss out!** Assemble your team (or go solo!) and be a part of shaping the future of AI agents. This hackathon welcomes projects at all stages to compete for prizes!

column14: Jon Turdiev is a Senior Solutions Architect at Amazon Web Services (AWS). He specializes in helping organizations design, build, and deploy cloud-based solutions on the AWS platform. His expertise lies in translating business requirements into scalable, secure, and cost-effective cloud architectures. Jon works directly with customers to understand their unique challenges and provide tailored guidance on leveraging AWS services to achieve their goals. He likely has experience with a wide range of AWS services, including compute, storage, databases, and networking.

About Event

# ‚ÄãAWS MCP Agents Hackathon

‚ÄãJoin us to build **cutting-edge AI agents** that push the limits of **LLMs and AI applications**!

# ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã **üéâ** üèÜ **$50k+ in Prizes!**

## ‚ÄãüöÄ The Challenge

‚ÄãUnleash your creativity to craft an extraordinary **multimodal AI agent!** Your mission is to design and develop an intelligent agent that's capable of sophisticated reasoning, strategic decision-making, and interacting with various tools. Build something that solves real problems and demonstrates innovative approaches to AI.

‚Äãüé§¬†**Showcase Your Vision:**

You will have¬†**3 minutes**¬†to captivate the audience and judges with your innovative solution. Pitch your AI agent‚Äôs purpose, capabilities, and transformative impact to win prizes.

## ‚Äã‚ÄãThe Opportunity

‚Äã‚Äã **Win big at this hackathon!** Compete for a chance to grab prizes and present your best product.

‚Äã‚Äã **Maximize your creation with sponsor APIs:** Many sponsors offer powerful APIs that can enhance your projects. Explore and utilize sponsor products to win special prizes.

‚Äã‚Äã **Join a vibrant community:** Connect with fellow AI engineers, learn from industry experts, and gain valuable exposure for your work.

‚Äã **Meet investors:** Network with investors who are interested in enterprise AI innovations. Gain feedback, connections, and potential funding.

‚Äã‚Äã **Don't miss out!** Assemble your team (or go solo!) and be a part of shaping the future of AI agents. This hackathon welcomes projects at all stages to compete for prizes!

column14: Saptarshi Banerjee is a Senior Solutions Architect at Amazon Web Services (AWS). He specializes in helping customers design, build, and deploy cloud solutions on the AWS platform. His expertise lies in areas like serverless computing, DevOps methodologies, and infrastructure automation. Saptarshi likely works closely with clients to understand their business requirements and translate them into scalable and secure cloud architectures. He plays a key role in guiding organizations through their cloud adoption journey.

column14: Ethan Dixon is a researcher at Anthropic, specializing in applied AI, particularly in areas like safety and interpretability. His work focuses on developing and implementing techniques to understand and control the behavior of large language models. He contributes to making these models more reliable and beneficial, addressing potential risks associated with their use. Dixon's research often involves exploring methods for aligning AI systems with human values. He aims to bridge the gap between theoretical AI safety research and practical deployment.

column14: Carolyn Ryan is a leader at Anthropic, focusing on Applied AI and go-to-market strategies. She's instrumental in translating Anthropic's foundational AI research into practical applications and real-world solutions for businesses. Her work involves bridging the gap between cutting-edge AI models and user needs, particularly around Claude. Ryan's expertise lies in understanding how AI can be effectively integrated into diverse industries and workflows. She plays a key role in shaping Anthropic's commercialization efforts and ensuring that their AI technology is accessible and valuable to a broad audience.

column14: Shreya Gupta is a Senior Developer Advocate at Auth0, focusing on empowering developers with authentication and authorization solutions. She possesses a deep understanding of identity management and its impact on application security. Shreya actively creates educational content, including tutorials and workshops, to simplify complex concepts for developers of all skill levels. Her advocacy extends to community engagement, where she fosters discussions and shares best practices. Ultimately, Shreya's goal is to help developers build secure and user-friendly applications with ease.

column14: Tony Holdstock-Brown is the Founder and CEO of Inngest, a serverless workflow engine designed to help developers build reliable background tasks. Before Inngest, he was a Senior Engineer at Vercel, where he focused on performance optimization and developer experience. Tony's passion lies in creating tools that simplify complex engineering challenges and empower developers. He brings a strong focus on user-friendliness and practical application to the world of distributed systems. His expertise stems from hands-on experience building and scaling large-scale applications.

column14: Upal Saha is the Co-founder and CTO of bem, a company focused on building innovative machine learning infrastructure solutions. He possesses extensive experience in distributed systems, data engineering, and machine learning operations (MLOps). At bem, he spearheads the technical vision and development of platforms designed to streamline and optimize the machine learning lifecycle for enterprises. Prior to bem, Upal held engineering roles at prominent tech companies. His work reflects a commitment to making machine learning more accessible and efficient for businesses of all sizes.

column14: Jason Shum is a Tech Advisor at MiniMax, a Chinese AI company specializing in large language models and multimodal AI. He is a veteran AI scientist known for his expertise in areas like natural language processing and deep learning. Shum plays a crucial role in guiding MiniMax's research and development, contributing to their advancements in generative AI. His experience helps shape the strategic direction of MiniMax's technological innovations. He likely provides valuable insights to the development and improvement of the company's core AI technologies.

column14: Nikhil Pareek is the Founder and CEO of Future AGI, a research company focused on building generally intelligent systems. His background is in physics and machine learning. He previously worked at Google Research on deep learning and artificial intelligence. Future AGI's approach centers on creating systems capable of reasoning and problem-solving across diverse tasks. He aims to create AI systems that can learn and adapt like humans.

column14: Priyanka Tembey is the Co-Founder and CTO of Operant AI, a company focused on building autonomous agents and large language model (LLM) infrastructure. She's a deep learning researcher specializing in reinforcement learning and LLMs. Her work emphasizes practical applications of AI to solve real-world problems. Before Operant AI, Priyanka held research positions focusing on developing and scaling AI technologies. She is passionate about making AI more reliable and effective.

He plays a key role in overseeing operations, driving strategic growth, and fostering strong relationships within the company. Toledano has a background in technology and a passion for improving the way businesses find and manage their workforce. He is dedicated to building innovative solutions that address the challenges of modern recruitment and staffing. His leadership contributes to Linkup's mission of providing efficient and reliable talent acquisition services.

column14: Venkat Thiruvengadam is the Founder and CEO of DuploCloud, a company focused on simplifying cloud infrastructure automation. He has a background in software engineering and a passion for enabling developers to easily build and deploy applications in the cloud. Prior to DuploCloud, Venkat held leadership roles at companies like Microsoft and Oracle, gaining extensive experience in cloud computing and platform development. His vision for DuploCloud is centered on a low-code/no-code approach to infrastructure management, allowing teams to accelerate their cloud adoption. Thiruvengadam's focus is on empowering companies to achieve greater agility and innovation through streamlined cloud operations.

He helps businesses understand and implement Make's capabilities to optimize their operations. With a background in technology solutions, he's adept at identifying client needs and crafting bespoke automation strategies. He translates technical jargon into practical solutions, empowering users to build complex integrations without code. Jonathan's expertise lies in demonstrating how Make can streamline processes and improve overall efficiency.

He is dedicated to fostering a strong and supportive ecosystem for Snowflake users.

column14: Sue Xu is a Managing Partner at Amino Capital, a venture capital firm specializing in early-stage investments in data-driven technologies, particularly in AI, cloud computing, and cybersecurity. With a PhD in Quantum Physics, she brings a deep technical understanding to her investment decisions. Xu focuses on supporting founders building transformative businesses and has a portfolio that includes companies across diverse sectors. Her expertise spans both science and business, making her a valuable asset in evaluating and nurturing innovative startups. She is known for her hands-on approach and dedication to fostering long-term partnerships.

column14: Chris McCann is a General Partner at Race Capital, a venture capital firm focusing on early-stage investments in infrastructure and developer tools. He co-founded Startup Digest, a popular email newsletter covering startup events globally, which was later acquired by Techstars. McCann has experience in community building and fostering developer ecosystems. His investment focus includes web3, fintech, and artificial intelligence infrastructure. He leverages his background to help portfolio companies navigate community growth and adoption challenges.

column14: Joli Zhang is a Partner at VU Venture Partners, focusing on early-stage investments in the enterprise SaaS, digital health, and consumer sectors. She has a strong background in data analytics and strategy, previously working at McKinsey & Company. Her investment focus includes leveraging AI and data-driven solutions to disrupt traditional industries. Joli actively supports portfolio companies with operational expertise and strategic guidance. She holds degrees from both the University of Pennsylvania and Harvard Business School.

About Event

‚ÄãDESIGN284: Design for Extended Realities is having its inaugural public exposition event this June! Come join us at the **Stanford** **[d.school](http://d.school/)** **in the Atrium**. Food and drinks provided.

[DESIGN284](https://dschool.stanford.edu/classes/designing-for-extended-realitites) is a quarter-long, project-based class focusing on developing emerging technology use cases in XR. Our diverse cohort of students ‚Äî from business, design, computer science, and education ‚Äî have spent the quarter conducting human-centered design research around problem areas and prototyping in XR with devices such as Snap Spectacles and Meta Quest 3.

‚ÄãIn this event, groups will be demonstrating and pitching their human-centered use cases and solutions. This will be an immersive and experiential time. Please try to arrive on time!

‚ÄãThis blend of computer science, design, and entrepreneurship is enriched by a 10-week learning journey with industry leaders and advisors at IDEO, Snap, Meta, Unity, and more.

‚ÄãXR industry practitioners, investors and judges will be in present. We look forward to seeing you there!

column14: Sarah Chung is the founder and CEO of Landing International, a company specializing in helping global beauty and wellness brands expand into the U.S. market. She's a seasoned entrepreneur with a deep understanding of the beauty industry and international business. Prior to Landing International, Chung held leadership roles at major beauty companies. Her expertise lies in distribution strategy, brand building, and navigating the complexities of the U.S. retail landscape. She's known for her strategic approach and ability to forge strong partnerships between brands and retailers.

column14: Payam Tabrizian is a technology leader and investor with a focus on AI and machine learning. He currently serves as a Partner at DCVC, a venture capital firm specializing in deep tech. Previously, he was a senior engineering leader at Google, where he oversaw various AI initiatives, including the development of the company's machine learning infrastructure. His expertise lies in building and scaling AI systems for real-world applications. Tabrizian holds a PhD in computer science from Stanford University.

column14: Yicheng "YC" Sun is a prominent figure in the Ethereum research and development community. He's known for his work on layer-2 scaling solutions, particularly Optimistic Rollups. YC contributes significantly to understanding and improving Ethereum's infrastructure, focusing on practical implementations. He's often involved in pushing the boundaries of what's possible in the blockchain space with innovative approaches to scalability. YC is highly regarded for his deep technical expertise and contributions to open-source projects.

column14: Ariane Lee is a Singaporean entrepreneur and tech investor focused on empowering Southeast Asian startups. She co-founded StyloPay, a mobile payments platform, and currently works with Golden Gate Ventures as a Principal. Lee actively mentors early-stage companies and advocates for increased diversity and inclusion within the tech ecosystem. Her expertise lies in fintech, e-commerce, and venture capital, with a passion for scaling innovative businesses in the region. She holds a degree in Electrical Engineering from the University of California, Berkeley.
